{"formatVersion":"1","manifest":{"primaryCategory":"Faith & Devotion","subcategory":"Sufism","audienceTags":["tradition:sufism","theme:wisdom","theme:justice","audience:morning"],"sortPriority":29,"groupingLevels":["work","chapter"],"groupingLabels":["Work","Chapter"],"dataPath":"Data/Collections/Saadi_Gulistan.json","supplementalDataPath":null,"languageCode":"en","displayNameEnglish":"Saadi — Gulistan & Bustan","script":"Latin","isRTL":false,"transliterationAvailable":false,"contentRating":"general","sourceId":"saadiGulistan","displayName":"Saadi — Gulistan & Bustan","version":"2.0","language":"English","edition":"Gladwin, Rehatsek Translations","type":"quotes","browseOrder":"sequence","itemCount":800,"supportsRandom":true,"supportsBrowse":true},"data":[{"id":"gulistan-1-1","text":"A king is like a shepherd; his country is the flock. Whoever is careless of the flock, his flocks will die.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 1, Story 1 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","story":"1"},"sequenceIndex":0,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-1-2","text":"He who sleeps on a full belly, when he awakes is refreshed; but he who sleeps fasting finds the morning of weariness.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 1, Story 2 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","story":"2"},"sequenceIndex":1,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-1-3","text":"In the eyes of the wise, an hour passed in obedience to God is worth more than all the treasures of the world.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 1, Story 3 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","story":"3"},"sequenceIndex":2,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-1-4","text":"Whoever tenders gentle advice to a friend should do so in private, not in public, for public censure is an insult.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 1, Story 4 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","story":"4"},"sequenceIndex":3,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-1-5","text":"Speak only when your words are better than silence.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 1, Story 5 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:solitude","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","story":"5"},"sequenceIndex":4,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-1-6","text":"The learned are like candles — they burn themselves to give light to others.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 1, Story 6 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","story":"6"},"sequenceIndex":5,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-1-7","text":"Better a wise enemy than a foolish friend.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 1, Story 7 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","story":"7"},"sequenceIndex":6,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-1-8","text":"Whoever is not merciful to the young cannot expect mercy from the old.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 1, Story 8 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","story":"8"},"sequenceIndex":7,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-2-1","text":"Four things are requisite for a contented life: good health, a wise heart, inner peace, and a faithful friend.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 2, Story 1 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:grief-healing","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","theme:mental-health","theme:mindfulness","theme:solitude","theme:wisdom","tradition:christianity","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"2","story":"1"},"sequenceIndex":8,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-2-2","text":"A man who speaks an unseasonable truth is either a fool or a very brave man.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 2, Story 2 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:courage","theme:love","theme:nature","theme:truth","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"2","story":"2"},"sequenceIndex":9,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-2-3","text":"Silence is the mark of wisdom; the more a man talks, the more likely he is to err.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 2, Story 3 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:solitude","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"2","story":"3"},"sequenceIndex":10,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-2-4","text":"One is not a man of knowledge because he can speak of many things; but he who is patient, and slow to speak, and quick to act.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 2, Story 4 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"2","story":"4"},"sequenceIndex":11,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-2-5","text":"It is not well for a man of understanding to tell all he knows, just as it is not well for a soldier to show all his weapons.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 2, Story 5 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"2","story":"5"},"sequenceIndex":12,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-3-1","text":"Consider the benefits of contentment. A wise man said: The whole earth is not enough for the soul that is not contented.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 3, Story 1 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","theme:nature","theme:self-knowledge","theme:wisdom","tradition:animism","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"3","story":"1"},"sequenceIndex":13,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-3-2","text":"Endure the unkindness of a friend, for one hour of pain is better than the loss of a friend forever.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 3, Story 2 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:grief-healing","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:grief","theme:love","theme:resilience","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"3","story":"2"},"sequenceIndex":14,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-3-3","text":"The wealth that has been gained by honest means is like a flowing river; use it with wisdom, and it will never dry up.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 3, Story 3 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:nature","theme:truth","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"3","story":"3"},"sequenceIndex":15,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-3-4","text":"Fear God though you see Him not, for He sees you.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 3, Story 4 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"3","story":"4"},"sequenceIndex":16,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-4-1","text":"Silence is the best reply to the fool.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 4, Story 1 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:solitude","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"4","story":"1"},"sequenceIndex":17,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-4-2","text":"It is better to sit alone than in company with the bad; and better to sit with a good man than alone.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 4, Story 2 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:solitude","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"4","story":"2"},"sequenceIndex":18,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-4-3","text":"Do not speak of the faults of those who are absent, for they cannot defend themselves.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 4, Story 3 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"4","story":"3"},"sequenceIndex":19,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-4-4","text":"Whoever confides a secret to one who is not trustworthy is himself untrustworthy.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 4, Story 4 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:relationships","theme:self-knowledge","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"4","story":"4"},"sequenceIndex":20,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-5-1","text":"Be kind to friends and enemies alike. The sun shines on all.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 5, Story 1 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"5","story":"1"},"sequenceIndex":21,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-5-2","text":"Cultivate the society of the wise; their very shadow is beneficial.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 5, Story 2 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"5","story":"2"},"sequenceIndex":22,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-5-3","text":"A good man is like a tree whose shade gives rest and whose fruit gives food. Cultivate such men.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 5, Story 3 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"5","story":"3"},"sequenceIndex":23,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-5-4","text":"Wisdom increases the more it is shared; gold diminishes the more it is divided.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 5, Story 4 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"5","story":"4"},"sequenceIndex":24,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-6-1","text":"It is better to sleep on the ground than to lean on an unsound support.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 6, Story 1 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"6","story":"1"},"sequenceIndex":25,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-6-2","text":"A wise man knows what is good; a foolish man knows what is pleasant.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 6, Story 2 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"6","story":"2"},"sequenceIndex":26,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-6-3","text":"Speak little; hear much; be not quick to speak but be quick to listen.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 6, Story 3 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"6","story":"3"},"sequenceIndex":27,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-7-1","text":"Speak gently to the young. The tongue that speaks the truth, though broken, is better than the tongue of falsehood, though golden.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 7, Story 1 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:grief-healing","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:truth","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"7","story":"1"},"sequenceIndex":28,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-7-2","text":"When you speak, let your words be few and your meaning clear.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 7, Story 2 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"7","story":"2"},"sequenceIndex":29,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-7-3","text":"He who works for the good of others sleeps in peace.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 7, Story 3 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"7","story":"3"},"sequenceIndex":30,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-8-1","text":"A contented man with a piece of bread is worth more than a thousand kings lamenting.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 8, Story 1 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"8","story":"1"},"sequenceIndex":31,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-8-2","text":"Thankfulness for benefits received is the best prayer.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 8, Story 2 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:gratitude","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:christianity","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"8","story":"2"},"sequenceIndex":32,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-8-3","text":"This world is a dream, and all the pleasures of sense are a dream within a dream.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 8, Story 3 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:solitude","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"8","story":"3"},"sequenceIndex":33,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-8-4","text":"The good man is not one who merely refrains from evil; the good man is one who actively seeks to do good.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 8, Story 4 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"8","story":"4"},"sequenceIndex":34,"isVerified":true},{"id":"gulistan-8-5","text":"It is easier to pull a stone out of a pond with a hook than to reclaim an evil habit from a man.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan, Chapter 8, Story 5 (Ross trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"chapter":"8","story":"5"},"sequenceIndex":35,"isVerified":true},{"id":"saadi-ext-000037","text":"He—in whose nature, is the ugly disposition Sees not the peacock,—only his ugly foot.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000038","text":"Have patience! All things are difficult before they become easy.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000039","text":"He who is a slave to his stomach seldom worships God.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000040","text":"To give pleasure to a single heart by a single kind act is better than a thousand head-bowings in prayer.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:christianity","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000041","text":"When the belly is empty, the body becomes spirit; when it is full, the spirit becomes body.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:animism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000042","text":"Every leaf of the tree becomes a page of the sacred scripture once the soul has learnt to read.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000043","text":"In the faculty of speech man excels the brute; but if thou utterest what is improper, the brute is thy superior.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000044","text":"There is a difference between him who claspeth his mistress in his arms, and him whose eyes are fixed on the door expecting her.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000045","text":"بنی آدم اعضای یک پیکرند که در آفرينش ز یک گوهرند چو عضوى به درد آورد روزگار دگر عضوها را نماند قرار تو کز محنت دیگران بی غمی نشاید که نامت نهند آدمیBanī 'ādam a'zā-ye yek peykar-and ke dar 'āfarīn-aš ze yek gowhar-and čo 'ozvī be dard āvarad rūzgār degar 'ozvhā-rā na-mānad qarār to k-az mehnat-ē dīgarān bīqam-ī na-šāyad ke nām-at nahand ādamī","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000046","text":"If thou covetest riches, ask not but for contentment, which is an immense treasure.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000047","text":"Use a sweet tongue, courtesy, and gentleness, and thou mayst manage to guide an elephant with a hair.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:leadership","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000048","text":"When gnats act in concert they will bring down an elephant: when ants set to work, and move in a body, they can strip a fierce lion of its hide.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000049","text":"Were the diver to think on the jaws of the shark, he would never lay hands on the precious pearl.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000050","text":"Whatever makes an impression on the heart seems lovely in the eye.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000051","text":"Science is for the cultivation of religion, not for worldly enjoyments.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000052","text":"Who despises an insignificant enemy resembles him who is careless about fire.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000053","text":"Whatever is produced in haste goes easily to waste.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000054","text":"Whenever you argue with another wiser than yourself, in order that others may admire your wisdom, they will discover your ignorance.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000055","text":"Whoever interrupts the conversation of others to make a display of his own fund of knowledge, makes notorious his own stock of ignorance.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000056","text":"Deep in the sea are riches beyond compare. But if you seek safety, it is on the shore.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000057","text":"A little and a little collected together becomes a great deal; the heap in the barn consists of single grains, and drop and drop form an inundation.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000058","text":"\"How hast thou so profound a lore attained?\" \"To ask another, I was ne’er ashamed.\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000059","text":"The wise man never heard a joke But living wisdom from it broke; The fool no wisdom ever learned But it in him to folly turned.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000060","text":"Each is bounded by his nature, And remains the same in stature, In the valley, on the mountain: Scoop from ocean or from fountain With a poor hand or a richer, You can only fill your pitcher.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000061","text":"Our condition is like the darting lightning, one instant flashing and the next disappearing. Sometimes we are seated above the fourth heaven, and at other times we cannot see the back of our feet.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000062","text":"He only has drunk the pure wine of unity who has forgotten, by remembering , all else in both worlds.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000063","text":"To pious minds, each verdant leaf displays A volume teeming with the Almighty’s praise.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000064","text":"A return of good for good is a slight reciprocity; but the true recompense is to confer benefits on him who has injured thee.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000065","text":"O brothers, Mecca is in front, and robbers in the rear. By proceeding, we escape; and, if we sleep, we die.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000066","text":"Not all the year, the vines their clusters keep: Now fruitful are, now leafy tears do weep. Sunlike, the pure are shadowed by a cloud; As sparks on water are the envious crowd: Those, by degrees, their former radiance shed; These are extinguished in a wat’ry bed. Fear not the dark, my friend, howe’er profound: Perchance therein life’s water may be found. Let not despair, though dark, thy soul dismay, For night is pregnant with the glorious day.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000067","text":"The beloved of the Almighty are the rich who have the humility of the poor, and the poor who have the magnanimity of the rich.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000068","text":"Take warning by the misfortunes of others, that others may not take example from you.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000069","text":"Let him who neglects to raise the fallen, fear lest, when he falls, no one will stretch out his hand to lift him up.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000070","text":"The rose and the thorn, and sorrow and gladness are linked together.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:grief-healing","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:grief","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000071","text":"That which is not allotted the hand cannot reach; and what is allotted you will find wherever you may be.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000072","text":"Capacity without education is deplorable, and education without capacity is thrown away.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000073","text":"O wise man, wash your hands of that friend who associates with your enemies.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000074","text":"The telling of a falsehood is like the cut of a sabre; for though the wound may heal, the scar of it will remain.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:grief-healing","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mental-health","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000075","text":"The bad fortune of the good turns their faces up to heaven; the good fortune of the bad bows their heads down to the earth.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:creativity","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:animism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000076","text":"Independence is of more value than any gifts; and to receive gifts is to lose it. — Men most commonly seek to oblige thee only that they may engage thee to serve them.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000077","text":"He who is a slave to his belly seldom worships God.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000078","text":"I fear God, and next to God I chiefly fear him who fears him not.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000079","text":"Nothing is so good for an ignorant man as silence; and if he was sensible of this he would not be ignorant.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000080","text":"A wise man in the company of those who are ignorant, has been compared to a beautiful girl in the company of blind men.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beauty","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000081","text":"A grateful dog is better than an ungrateful man.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:gratitude","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000082","text":"Two persons take trouble in vain, and use fruitless endeavors, — he who acquires wealth without enjoying it, and he who is taught wisdom but does not practice it. How much soever you may study science, when you do not act wisely you are ignorant. The beast whom they load with books is not profoundly learned and wise; what knoweth his empty skull whether he carrieth firewood or books?","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000083","text":"He who learns, and makes no use of his learning, is a beast of burden with a load of books. — Does the ass comprehend whether he carries on his back a library or a bundle of faggots?","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000084","text":"He who is intoxicated with wine will be sober again in the course of the night, but he who is intoxicated by the cup-bearer will not recover his senses until the day of judgment.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000085","text":"An enemy to whom you show kindness becomes your friend, excepting lust, the indulgence of which increases its enmity.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000086","text":"Obedience is not truly performed by the body, if the heart is dissatisfied.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000087","text":"Were the king at noonday to say, \"This day is night,\" it would behoove us to reply, \"Lo! there are the moon and seven stars!\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000088","text":"Nothing is so good for an ignorant man as silence; if he were sensible of this he would not be ignorant.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000089","text":"God gives sleep to the bad, in order that the good maybe undisturbed.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000090","text":"A traveller without observation is a bird without wings.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000091","text":"A little and a little, collected together, become a great deal; the heap in the barn consists of single grains, and drop and drop make the inundation.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000092","text":"He who learns the rules of wisdom without conforming to them in his life is like a man who ploughs in his field but does not sow.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000093","text":"A handsome woman is a jewel; a good woman is a treasure.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000094","text":"Abar gar ab-i-zindagi barad Hargiz az shakh-i-bed bar na khori Bar faromaya rozgar mabar Kaz nai boriya shakar nakhori.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000095","text":"Agar dunya na bashad, dardmandem Wa agar bashad, ba mihrash pae bandem Bala'e z'in jahan ashubtar nest Ki ranj-i-khatirast ar hast wa nest.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000096","text":"Agar sad sal gabar atish farozad Wa gar ek dam daru uftad basozad.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000097","text":"Ahanera ki morchana bikhurad Natawan burd azū basaiqal zang; Ba siyah dil che sud guftan w'az? Narawad mekh-i-ahanin dar sang.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000098","text":"Akibat gurg-zade gurg shavad Garche ba adami buzurg shavad.","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000099","text":"Recitation of Bani Adam in Persian by Amir H. Ghaseminejad","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000100","text":"\"Saadi\" in R. W. Emerson's Poems (1847)","author":"Saadi","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000101","text":"Produced by Cornell University, Joshua Hutchinson, Steve Schulze and the Online Distributed Proofreading Team.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000102","text":"Director of the Scientific Corps of the Western Union Telegraph Expedition.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000103","text":"Full Octavo, with nearly One Hundred Elegant Illustrations, engraved by the late JOHN ANDREW, from drawings by the Author.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000104","text":"This volume contains not only the record of a THREE YEARS residence in Alaska—made under the most favorable circumstances for explorations—but a complete history of the country gathered from every available source.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000105","text":"It is very full in details of Productions, Climate, Soil, Temperature, Language, the Manners and Customs of its peoples, etc., etc.; and is the most valuable, as well as the most authentic, addition to the history of Alaska.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:truth","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000106","text":"And is one of the most elegant books issued in America.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000107","text":"LEE & SHEPARD, Boston. TO NEWS-DEALERS. PUNCHINELLO'S MONTHLY. THE FIVE NUMBERS FOR APRIL, Bound in a Handsome Cover, Will be ready May 2d. Price, Fifty Cents. THE TRADE Supplied by the AMERICAN NEWS COMPANY, Who are now prepared to receive Orders. HARRISON BRADFORD & CO.'S STEEL PENS.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000108","text":"These pens are of a finer quality, more durable, and cheaper than any other Pen in the market. Special attention is called to the following grades, as being better suited for business purposes than any Pen manufactured. The","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000109","text":"\"505,\" \"22,\" and the \"Anti-Corrosive.\" We recommend for bank and office use. D. APPLETON & CO., Sole Agents for United States.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000110","text":"_CONANT'S PATENT BINDERS for \"Punchinello,\" to preserve the paper for binding, will be sent, postpaid, on receipt of One Dollar, by \"Punchinello Publishing Company,\" 83 Nassau Street, New-York City._","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000111","text":"APPLICATIONS FOR ADVERTISING IN \"PUNCHINELLO\" SHOULD BE ADDRESSED TO J. NICKINSON, Room No. 4, 83 NASSAU STREET. HERCULES MUTUAL","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000112","text":"THOMAS H. WHITE, M.D., Medical Examiner.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000113","text":"Mercantile Library, Clinton Hall, Astor Place New-York.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000114","text":"This is now the largest circulating Library In America, the number of volumes on its shelves being 114,000.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000115","text":"About 1000 volumes are added each month; and very large purchases are made of all new and popular works.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000116","text":"Books are delivered at members' residences for five cents each delivery.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000117","text":"TERMS OF MEMBERSHIP: TO CLERKS, $1 Initiation, $3 Annual Dues.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000118","text":"76 CEDAR STREET, NEW-YORK, AND AT Yonkers, Norwalk, Stamford, and Elizabeth.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000119","text":"HIRAM WOODRUFF on the TROTTING HORSE OF AMERICA!","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000120","text":"With Reminiscenses of the Trotting Turf. A handsome 12mo, with a splendid steel-plate portrait of Hiram Woodruff. Price, extra cloth, $2.25.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000121","text":"The New-York Tribune says: _\"This is a Masterly Treatise by the Master of his Profession_—the ripened product of forty years' experience in Handling, Training, Riding, and Driving the Trotting Horse. There is no book like it in any language on the subject of which it treats.\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000122","text":"Bonner says in the _Ledger_, \"It is a book for which every man who owns a horse ought to subscribe. The information which it contains is worth ten times its cost.\" For sale by all booksellers, or single copies sent postpaid on receipt of price. Agents wanted.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000123","text":"J. B. FORD & CO, Printing-House Square, New-York. Thomas J. Rayner & Co., 29 LIBERTY STREET, New-York, MANUFACTURERS OF THE _Finest Cigars made in the United States._","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000124","text":"All sizes and styles. Prices very moderate. Samples sent to any responsible house. Also Importers of the","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000125","text":"\"FUSBOS\" BRAND, Equal in quality to the best of the Havana market, and from ten to twenty per cent cheaper.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000126","text":"Restaurant, Bar, Hotel, and Saloon trade will save money by calling at 29 LIBERTY STREET PUNCHINELLO.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000127","text":"With a large and varied experience in the management and publication of a paper of the class herewith submitted, and with the still more positive advantage of an Ample Capital to justify the undertaking, the","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000128","text":"PUNCHINELLO PUBLISHING CO. OF THE CITY OF NEW-YORK, Presents to the public for approval, the NEW ILLUSTRATED HUMOROUS AND SATIRICAL WEEKLY PAPER, PUNCHINELLO, The first number of which will be issued under date of April 2.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000129","text":"PUNCHINELLO will be entirely original; humorous and witty, without vulgarity, and satirical without malice.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000130","text":"It will be printed on a superior tinted paper of sixteen pages, size 13 by 9, and will be for sale by all respectable newsdealers who have the judgment to know a good thing when they see it, or by subscription from this office.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000131","text":"Suitable for the paper, and Original Designs, or suggestive ideas or sketches for illustrations, upon the topics of the day, are always acceptable, and will be paid for liberally.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000132","text":"Rejected communications can not be returned, unless postage stamps are inclosed.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000133","text":"TERMS: One copy, per year, in advance $4.00 Single copies, ten cents. A specimen copy will be mailed free upon the receipt of ten cents. One copy, with the Riverside Magazine, or any other magazine or paper, price $2.50, for 5.50","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000134","text":"One copy, with any magazine or paper, price $4, for 7.00 All communications, remittances, etc., to be addressed to PUNCHINELLO PUBLISHING CO., No.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000135","text":"_(For terms to Clubs, see 16th page.)_ AMERICAN BUTTONHOLE, OVERSEAMING, AND SEWING-MACHINE CO., 563 Broadway, New-York.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000136","text":"This great combination machine is the last and greatest improvement on all former machines, making, in addition to all work done on best Lock-Stitch machines, beautiful","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:action","theme:beauty","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000137","text":"BUTTON AND EYELET HOLES; in all fabrics. Machine, with finely finished OILED WALNUT TABLE AND COVER","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000138","text":"complete, $75. Same machine, without the buttonhole parts, $60. This last is beyond all question the simplest, easiest to manage and to keep in order, of any machine in the market. Machines warranted, and full instruction given to purchasers.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000139","text":"Has just received a large assortment of all the latest styles of Chignons, Chatelaines, etc.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000140","text":"Comprising the following beautiful varieties:","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beauty","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000141","text":"La Coquette, La Plenitude, Le Bouquet, La Sirene, L'Imperatrice, etc.,","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000142","text":"At prices varying from $2 upward. HENRY SPEAR STATIONER, PRINTER AND BLANK BOOK MANUFACTURER. ACCOUNT BOOKS MADE TO ORDER. PRINTING OF EVERY DESCRIPTION. 82 Wall Street, NEW-YORK. WEVILL & HAMMAR, Wood Engravers, No. 208 BROADWAY, NEW-YORK.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000143","text":"Illustration: YE YONGE MANNE OF MANHATTAN","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000144","text":"Ye Yonge Manne is born, and his parents hasten with him to ye abode of ye BROWN, praying that he may be christened among ye upper tenne.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:christianity","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000145","text":"And when ye Yonge Manne takes a daughter of ye upper tenne to wife, ye BROWN sees that he is married in ye BROWN his church.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000146","text":"Ye BROWN demands if ye parents put in their coal in ye Summer time; and, being told that they do, he has ye Yonge Manne christened in his church, and when he grows up ye BROWN introduces him into Society.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:christianity","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000147","text":"And when ye Yonge Manne he dies, ye BROWN arranges with all ye gardeners and black-goods men. And so, ye Yonge Manne, he is done entirely BROWN.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000148","text":"Suppose I were a father— A luckless wight, called \"Pa\"!","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000149","text":"I'd say, \"Now curse the restless rover That first (despising clover!) Invented Moving-day!\" O yes!","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000150","text":"Especially, if moving Was likely to be proving (As usual) a mess!","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000151","text":"Sure to be smashed to particles, Or \"snaked off\" with a \"hook\"!","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000152","text":"You've got Chairs, bedsteads, tables, crockery— (Recital seems a mockery!) You've got—what have you not?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000153","text":"What's worse, Your things won't fit new places, Your wife won't like new faces— Your very maid will curse!","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000154","text":"think of that, And think Of possible colds and fevers— Cartmen that prove deceivers— Nothing to eat or drink!","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000155","text":"Tired of one thing only: But they escape all this!","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000156","text":"And pray, What man with sons and daughters Don't sigh for bachelor quarters About the First of May?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000157","text":"Printed, according to Act of Congress, in the year 1870, by the PUNCHINELLO PUBLISHING COMPANY, in the Clerk's Office of the District Court of the United States, for the Southern District of New York.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000158","text":"At the Banquet of the Army of the Potomac in Philadelphia, Mr.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000159","text":"DANIEL DOUGHERTY made one of the most extraordinary speeches on record, if we except certain forensic efforts of Mr.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000160","text":"PUNCHINELLO delivered during the earlier stages of his career from his box.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000161","text":"DOUGHERTY is a Soarer, and a Spreader, and a Screamer.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000162","text":"Speaking metaphorically, be goes higher, measures more from the tip of one wing to the other, and is more suggestive of the warbling of a locomotive in his speech than any other Eagle in Philadelphia, which is saying a great deal.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000163","text":"DANIEL is a Giant of Rhetoric, and would remind us of the Big Gentleman from Cardiff, only that mysterious personage is too heavy to Soar; for which reason he usually occupies the ground floor, which Mr.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000164","text":"DOUGHERTY does not do by any manner of means.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000165","text":"It was this extraordinary capacity of Mr.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000166","text":"DOUGHERTY for Soaring which caused him to be called upon by the Army of the Potomac for a speech.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000167","text":"begins by declaring that he would rather speak for his country than for Pennsylvania, which, considering that he also declared that he came \"as a modest spectator,\" does not strike us as the depth of humility.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000168","text":"D., \"is not confined to any locality;\" and we believe that Mr.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000169","text":"PECKSNIFF said something like this of his own frontal linen.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000170","text":"DOUGHERTY does for a chest when his own has gone upon its extensive journeys; something temporary is done, we suppose, with a pad.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000171","text":"But the Bosom was at the Banquet, and the proprietor was there to thump it, until it must have sounded and reverberated; and if Mr.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000172","text":"DOUGHERTY had also thumped his head, there would have been equal evidence of hollowness within.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000173","text":"\"May my tongue never prove a traitor!\" cried the orator.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000174","text":"The tongue is well enough, and is likely to be.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000175","text":"It's something a little higher up that is likely to give out.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000176","text":"If the applause of the brave men before him was what Mr.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:courage","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000177","text":"DOUGHERTY wanted, (besides his dinner,) then of applause he got the Stomach under his Bosom full.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000178","text":"The speech was received, according to the reporters, with a roaring which has not been equalled since the Lions in the Den roared at the other DANIEL, until they found that the good man was neither to be roared or sneezed at with impunity.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000179","text":"The cheering was \"tremendous.\" The cheering was \"terrific.\" The cheering was \"prolonged.\" And there stood \"the Bosom not confined to any locality,\" but just then swelling, and expanding, and dilating—shall we for once be fine, and say like an Ocean Billow?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000180","text":"Voices which shouted at Gettysburg now hailed Mr.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000181","text":"DANIEL DOUGHERTY as a Conquering Hero—the conqueror of their cars!","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000182","text":"Once in a while there was \"great laughter\" when Mr.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000183","text":"hadn't said any thing specially funny—that is, if Mr.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000184","text":"PUNCHINELLO is a judge of fun; and if he isn't, who in all the world is?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000185","text":"There are two kinds of laughter—the laughing at and the laughing with; and we have known \"tremendous\" and even \"vociferous\" applause to be very suspicious.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000186","text":"It must be a source of calm satisfaction to General GRANT to know that he is considered the \"great and glorious GRANT\" by Mr.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000187","text":"DANIEL DOUGHERTY; although DANIEL once considered Mr.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000188","text":"to be equally \"great and glorious.\" So DANIEL also considers SHERMAN to be \"immortal,\" and SHERIDAN \"unconquerable,\" and MEADE \"glorious.\" Adjectives are cheap, you know; and D.D., Esq., has evidently a great stock of them in his Wandering Bosom.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mortality","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000189","text":"Only, great soldiers, who know the precise value of Mr.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000190","text":"DOUGHERTY'S military opinions, might not care to have them laid on too thickly.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000191","text":"DOUGHERTY'S Family Doctor to inquire into the state of Mr.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:relationships","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000192","text":"D's health after this tremendous effort, and he sends us a bulletin that Mr.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:grief-healing","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:mental-health","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000193","text":"is \"as well as could be expected.\" We do not know what he means by this; it seems to us to lack scientific precision.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000194","text":"The point upon which we wished to be informed was, whether Mr.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000195","text":"did or did not break any thing—not the tumblers on the table, for that we should expect; but any thing in the way of blood-vessels.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000196","text":"Not to put too fine a point upon it, How's the Bosom?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000197","text":"The great pride, the _dulce decus_ of Americans, has long been in their pocket hardware, and the skill with which they use it.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000198","text":"But we must henceforth look to our laurels.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000199","text":"France is competing alarmingly with us in the use of the revolver.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000200","text":"They were always a revolutionary people, were the French, and revolving seems, therefore, to suit their temper to a T, (Gunpowder T, of course.) Since the slaying of NOIR by BONAPARTE, the affectation of readiness with the pistol has become quite the thing in Paris.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000201","text":"New-York and Paris will soon be exactly alike in the bullet business—especially Paris.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000202","text":"PAUL DE CASSAGNAC, it seems, has been invited by some anonymous person to meet him at a certain hour in front of the _mairie_ of the Seventeenth _arrondissement_, for the purpose of having his brains removed with a revolver.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000203","text":"The _Mairie_ mentioned in the cartel was not the one for PAUL.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000204","text":"Probably he would have gone to VIRGINIA, had he been invited to do so; but never a MAIRIE for the faithful PAUL.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:christianity","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000205","text":"And might have come by way of New-York, where he would soon have grown so used to having his brains removed with a revolver that the process would have become a pleasure to him.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000206","text":"PUNCHINELLO cannot help liking Philadelphia, and always feels a pang of sympathy whenever any thing happens to that plain old city.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000207","text":"One reason for this is, (and he is not ashamed of the weakness,) that Philadelphia likes PUNCHINELLO and takes, weekly, he would not be vain enough to say how many hundred copies of his journal.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000208","text":"And now Philamaclink, as her natives love to call her, is afflicted with a terrible disease—a fearful attack of chronic Legislature.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000209","text":"Even when the active symptoms of this dread malady have subsided, the effects linger, and the consequent suffering is excruciating.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000210","text":"One of the direst of the effects of the last attack is a dreadful bill—not a bile—which has caused a utilization sewage company to appear upon her body corporate.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000211","text":"It is almost impossible for sister cities to understand the torments of such an affliction.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000212","text":"Nobody can now clear away their own dirt—Councils, Board of Health, or any body else.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:grief-healing","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mental-health","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000213","text":"Even the birds in the squares must not cleanse their nests without a printed permit from the company.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000214","text":"If a bedstead is cleaned, the company must have the bugs.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000215","text":"Only one dirty thing is safe from this all-powerful corporation, and that is the legisiative delegation from the city.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000216","text":"If the refuse matter were taken from that, there would be nothing left.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000217","text":"It has been proposed that the Legislature itself should be purified; but this idea is Utopian, PUNCHINELLO fears.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000218","text":"If Niagara were squirted through its halls, the water would be dirtied, but the halls would not be cleansed.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000219","text":"Trampled under the heels of the aristocratic HONG and PENNY BUNN, what is there to hope for it?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000220","text":"There are about eight hundred thousand inhabitants in the place.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000221","text":"Some twenty thousand of these owe small sums for unpaid taxes, averaging about nine and a quarter cents to a man.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000222","text":"To collect these sums, an army of seventy-two thousand able-bodied men, at salaries of one thousand dollars per annum, has been commissioned by the PENNY BUNN Legislature.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000223","text":"A private firm has prevailed upon the imbecile old farmers from the western and interior counties to give them the right to build a private freight railroad through many of the principal streets of the Quaker City.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000224","text":"This road will run through several school-house yards, and the time-tables are to be so arranged that trains shall always be due at those points at recess time.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000225","text":"Every fiftieth private house along the lines is to have a road-station and freight-depot in its front-parlor, and all male residents on said routes are to serve in turn, without pay, as brakesmen and switch-tenders.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000226","text":"The owners of all vehicles injured by the trains are to be heavily fined, and the families of individuals allowing themselves to be killed are to be mulcted in heavy damages.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000227","text":"A counterfeit tax-bill has been passed by the Legislature.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000228","text":"All the sums handed in to the State Treasury by the tax collectors have been found to be \"bogus\" money.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000229","text":"This action has been indorsed by the Legislature, and the action of that body is hereafter to be of the same character as the funds paid in by its creatures.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000230","text":"Alas, poor city! But all has not yet been told. Colonel FORNEY intends resuming his \"Occasional\" letters in the _Press!_","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000231","text":"When the Governor or President V-toes a bill, is he supposed to put his foot on it?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000232","text":"SPECTACLES are proverbially fit for old eyes.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:animism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000233","text":"Probably that is the reason why the spectacle of the _Twelve Temptations_ is so dear to the aged eyes of the gray-haired old gentlemen who occupy the front seats at the Grand Opera House.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000234","text":"It is certainly a brilliant spectacle, though, like the ideal scene to which Mrs.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000235","text":"Why, then, should the stern advocate of the legitimate drama refuse to acknowledge that the _Twelve Temptations_ has its redeeming legs?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000236","text":"How runs the ancient proverb, \"Singed milk is better than it looks;\" or that equally ancient philosophical maxim, \"There is no use in crying over spilt cats\"?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:animism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000237","text":"The stupid story of ULRIC'S folly is made more attractive than one would suppose that it could be, and we need not weep over the fact that it is a spectacle, and not a SHAKESPEAREAN tragedy.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000238","text":"_Act 1. Curtain rises upon a score of Unintelligible Demons_, who sing this impressive chorus:","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000239","text":"\"Oh! um um um um For um um um um And um um um um To um um um um.\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000240","text":"_Exeunt Demons. Enter_ RUDOLPH THE TEMPTER. _He remarks to the surrounding scenery_—\"ULLERIC'S soul must be mine, or else the dark abodes of torment await me. I will tempt him. Great Master, appear.\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000241","text":"_The Great Master—a major-general of fiends—appears, and, approving of_ RUDOLPH'S _virtuous resolve, they descend to—well, they descend below the Erie Building, to drink to his success.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000242","text":"Enter_ ULRIC _and family, including Aged Mother, Virtuous Heroine, Hated Rival, and Demoniac Servant._","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:leadership","theme:love","theme:relationships","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000243","text":"ULRIC. \"Motherr, this slife is intollerrabble; I will do any thing to escape frrrom it.\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000244","text":"_Enter_ RUDOLPH _and Unintelligible Demons (disguised.) They sing as before._","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000245","text":"ULRIC. \"The song says terruly. I will go with you, though you were the fiend himself.\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000246","text":"_Consternation on the part of every one. Demoniac Servant remarks, \"Ha! ha!\"_ ULRIC _and the Demons sink through the floor. Scene changes to the Studio of Eblis._","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:leadership","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000247","text":"Whatever you wish you shall have at the price of five years of your life.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000248","text":"A stripe will vanish each time your wish is gratified.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000249","text":"(_Aside._) The stripes are only cloth, you know, and you can pull 'em off when your back is turned to the audience.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000250","text":"ULRIC. \"It 'er is.\" (_Malignant crash from the orchestra._)","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000251","text":"RUDOLPH. \"ULLERIC, 'tis well. Now thou shall behold our sports.\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000252","text":"_Enter ballet girls, dressed in red gaiters and torches.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000253","text":"They dance the Demon Cancan, waving their torches and scattering the flames.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000254","text":"Old Gentleman, in the front row hears such charming little asides as, \"Drat you,_ MARY SMITH, _you've burnt my hand.\" \"I'll slap your face, Miss, if you step on my foot again.\" \"O_ NELLY!","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000255","text":"Curtain finally falls upon a blaze of light and a bewildering wealth of legs.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000256","text":"_Old Gentleman, in front row._ \"Well, he! he! that's pretty good; he! he! Devilish pretty girls some of 'em; he! he!\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000257","text":"_Virtuous Matron._ \"My dear, isn't it shameful. I never saw any thing so disgusting.\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000258","text":"_Sceptical Husband._ \"Then perhaps we'd better go at once.\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000259","text":"_Virtuous Matron._ \"N—no. I'll sit through one more act, and see if it gets any worse.\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000260","text":"_Fast Young Man._ \"They're all padded, you know. You can't feel sure about one of 'em. There were gals in the _Crook_ who used to pad their's from here to here\"—(_adds explanatory pantomime._)","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000261","text":"_Travelled Man, who has been to Paris._ \"These girls can't dance, I assure you. Now, at the Châtelet they do these things differently.\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000262","text":"_Admiring Friend to Travelled Man._ \"What spectacles did you see at the Châtelet?\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000263","text":"_Travelled Man,_ (who was in Paris only two days, and never saw even the outside of the theatre.) \"It was—let me see—Oh! _Moses in Egypt_ was the name of the piece. It was gorgeous; full of Egyptian scenery, and Egyptian dancing girls and things.\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000264","text":"_Admiring Friend, (with aggravating persistence.)_ \"Do you mean Rossini's _Moses_?\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:resilience","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000265","text":"_Travelled Man, (quite desperate.)_ \"Of course! He's the rival of OFFENBACH, you know. But come, let's go and take something.\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000266","text":"(_They go, the faith of the Admiring Friend in the Travelled Man's veracity being, however, perceptibly shaken._)","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:christianity","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000267","text":"ULRIC makes a dozen wishes, all of which are gratified, and all of which have the inevitable effect of transporting him into scenes pervaded by the female leg to an extent that easily reconciles him to the successive loss of five years of his life.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:grief-healing","audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:action","theme:grief","theme:love","tradition:sufism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000268","text":"He finally becomes King of Egypt, and, after having fought against the Crusaders in defence of those well-known Mohammedan gods, ISIS and OSIRIS, is carried down a trap by exulting demons.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000269","text":"An Intolerable Comic Man opens up hitherto unknown wastes of dreariness, and sings a comic song that is positively more tedious than an article from the _Nation_.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000270","text":"The Demoniac Servant is continually shot up through spring traps, in order to remark, \"Ha!","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:leadership","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000271","text":"ha!\" and to immediately disappear again.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000272","text":"The Aged Mother travels from Flanders to Egypt without changing her dress or combing her back hair, for the vain purpose of begging \"ULLERIC\" to repent.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000273","text":"Consumptive Knights fight terrific broad-sword duels with a thirst for combat that beer alone is subsequently able to allay.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000274","text":"The Virtuous HEROINE displays a very neat pair of ankles, but without winning \"ULLERIC\" from the devil of his ways.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000275","text":"Half a dozen ballets are successively introduced, in which the skirts of the dancers are seen to decrease as rapidly and steadily as the stripes on ULRIC'S magic collar.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000276","text":"Finally, a grand Transformation Scene, which has nothing whatever to do with the play, exhibits the best legs of the company in the most favorable attitudes, and the green baize curtain falls upon the great spectacle of the day.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000277","text":"_Virtuous Matron._ \"Well, I never! It's positively indecent. I'd like to take a whip to those shameless hussies.\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000278","text":"_Sceptical Husband._ \"PAGE offered me a proscenium box the other day. Suppose we take it to-morrow night?\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000279","text":"_Virtuous Matron._ \"I'll go to please you, my dear. And really the scenery is pretty.\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000280","text":"_Wretched Man, who is shameless enough to admit that he likes it._ \"I like it.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000281","text":"The ballet's good, the scenery is splendid, and the music might be worse.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000282","text":"Why don't these ladies, who come here and sit it through, have the honesty to admit that they come because they like it?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:truth","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000283","text":"But no; they go away, and at the next party, where they wear dresses lower in the neck than any I've seen on the stage to night, they'll abuse the poor girls who have danced here for their amusement.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000284","text":"Their malignant modesty does not deserve the respect of an intelligent _figurante_.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000285","text":"If they are sincere, why do they come here?\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:truth","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000286","text":"Which question still puzzles the perturbed mind of _MATADOR_.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000287","text":"We clip the following from the _Express_:","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000288","text":"\"There seem to be more legal loopholes for convicted murderers to escape through than for any other class of criminals.\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000289","text":"That is too true, by a great deal. There should be but one \"legal loophole\" for a convicted murderer, and the authorities should not let him escape through the loop of it—they should Knot.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000290","text":"[Illustration: A MOVING INCIDENT. _Pat, (to Bridget.)_ “TAKE YOUR MASTHER’S TRUNK TO THE RAILROAD, IS IT? OCH! BOTHER—DON’T YOU SEE I’M MOVIN’ A FAMILY?”]","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:relationships","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000291","text":"For genial law-making in America commend us to the Ohio House of Representatives.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000292","text":"Shall we hear of any sympathy for Cuba in that quarter?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000293","text":"\"My Darling, I have found a panacea for all woes, In Man:","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000294","text":"The Great PUNCHINELLO dinner has come off!","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000295","text":"JENKINS was there, and was to have telegraphed an account.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000296","text":"But he was not so well as usual the next day, the Thames water having got into his head.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000297","text":"So your correspondent is obliged to trust to his memory—unaffected by the water, which he did not take.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:relationships","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000298","text":"Old London Tavern was the scene of this banquet, given by the _literati_ of England in honor of the long-wished-for coming of PUNCHINELLO.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000299","text":"The dining-hall was decorated for the occasion with appropriate portraits.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000300","text":"There were HOGARTH, CERVANTES, ADDISON, MOLIÈRE, SWIFT, STERNE, GOLDSMITH, TOM HOOD, IRVING, THACKERAY, DICKENS, and ARTEMUS WARD.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000301","text":"A number of the waiters were costumed in character.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000302","text":"From my seat, I recognized SAM WELLER, (right behind me;) the Fat Boy of _Pickwick;_ SANCHO PANZA, and JEAMES YELLOWPLUSH.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000303","text":"PUNCH was represented at the head of the table so well that you could know him at once from his weekly frontispiece.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000304","text":"On one side of him sat CHARLES DICKENS; on the other, your humble ambassador.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000305","text":"It would be rather invidious to name the other hundred guests; not to be there was to be nowhere in literature.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000306","text":"Near me there sat Lord LYTTON, TOM HUGHES, PRÉVOST PARADOL, EDMOND ABOUT, CHARLES KINGSLEY, PAUL FÉVAL, and the Rev.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:christianity","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000307","text":"PUNCH how the latter very staid individual came to be there, I understood that, of all the absurd men of this century, he was selected as the most representatively preposterous.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000308","text":"The PRINCE OF WALES was not asked, lest his morals might be hurt by something that was said.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000309","text":"And it is so important, you know, for the British nation—(for the rest, see the _Saturday Review_.) And then Madame GEORGE SAND was to be there, who sometimes wears trowsers.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000310","text":"MATTHEW ARNOLD was spoken to about it; but he replied gruffly,","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000311","text":"\"PUNCHINELLO is Goliath of the Philistines!\" and declined.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000312","text":"JOHN STUART MILL was too busy over his next book, which is to be \"On the Subjection of Horses.\" But every body else was there, so we did not miss these grave and reverend seigniors.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000313","text":"How the twenty-five courses came on and went off, from the ox-tail soup and salmon to the dessert, it would need the tongue or pen of SOYER or PIERRE BLOT to narrate; as it needed the capacity of a FALSTAFF to do justice to them.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:justice","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000314","text":"And then, when the cover was removed, came the time of trial to your correspondent.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000315","text":"\"The Queen\" and \"the President\" were drunk with all the honors.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000316","text":"PUNCH called out, through his magnificent old nose, so that you might have heard him across the Channel, \"Health and long life to PUNCHINELLO!\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:grief-healing","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mental-health","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000317","text":"Now, your correspondent had remembered Mr.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000318","text":"HAWTHORNE'S experience at a Lord Mayor's dinner, and had begged Mr.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:christianity","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000319","text":"PUNCH by all means to let him off without a speech.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000320","text":"But, more worldly-wise than HAWTHORNE, he didn't believe that Mr.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000321","text":"PUNCH is going to have the speech published in pamphlet form, for distribution among his numerous constituents.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000322","text":"The PRINCE OF MONACO has declared war against France. OLLIVIER proposes to send the PRINCE IMPERIAL to extinguish him with a corps of infantry, armed with popguns; no one to be admitted to the corps who is more than four years old. MONACO aspires to be a sort of LOPEZ.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000323","text":"Sultan ABDUL AZIZ has just had a visit from a friend of JOHN BRIGHT'S.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000324","text":"To the surprise of every body, even his most intimate friends, the Sultan immediately made up his mind to turn Quaker!","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000325","text":"He came down stairs, and went into mosque, the other day, with a broad-brimmed hat, straight coat, and drab trowsers; and insisted on all the ladies of his _hareem_ putting on plain bonnets, and holding a \"silent meeting\" in the Seraglio!","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000326","text":"How it bothered them to do that last thing you may well suppose!","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000327","text":"SECRETARY FISH is said to preserve a decidedly spruce appearance at the State Dinners. Fish is nothing if not Fin-ical.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000328","text":"The sight of a thick, four-pound steak, just cut from a halibut that must have weighed, (the idea of a fish wading!) some two hundred pounds, reminds us that trout-fishing is just now in full operation.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000329","text":"What a strange, weird mystery there is about mental associations!","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000330","text":"Long, long ago, we possessed a favorite trout-rod fitted with a Hollow Butt, and so it is that whenever we see a Halibut, trouting comes to our mind.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000331","text":"Yesterday, frogs were croaking, and insects all in green livery, with gilt buttons, contributed to Nature's Great Boston Jubilee of music with their hum. How ridiculous it seems that insects should have a hum!—and yet the Bee has its Hum in its hive.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000332","text":"It is at this season that enthusiastic anglers always get water on the brain.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000333","text":"They have visions of mill-ponds, with beautiful little cascades sluicing into them over dams.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beauty","theme:leadership","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000334","text":"They stand, in imagination, on bridges, in the eddies beneath which they discern the wagging of silvery tails and rosy fins; and a very common form of nightmare with them is to fancy that the reel of the fishing-rod won't work, just as they are going to wind up a four-pound trout.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000335","text":"Now, also, is the time when friend gives much advice to friend on the subject of the \"gentle art.\" (A trout's opinion on this branch of art, by the by, would be worth having. Perhaps he might not consider it so gentle.)","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000336","text":"One student of the angle will say to another, \"Always fish up the stream. Fish lie with their heads to the current and their tails in the opposite direction: therefore, by casting up-stream, you run the less chance of being seen by them.\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000337","text":"Another says, \"Be sure you make your casts down-stream; your bob-flies like it better, as you can see by the way they dance on the ripples.\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000338","text":"Quoth another, \"Always soak your casting-lines with water before you start for the river-side;\" while a fourth instructs you never to straighten your lines with water, but by passing them through a piece of India rubber doubled between the finger and thumb.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:action","theme:creativity","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000339","text":"_Our_ advice is, Never cast against the wind.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000340","text":"In fact, you can't do it; and if you try it, you run the risk of getting _strabismus_—that is, the Cast in your eye.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000341","text":"Artificial flies, like artificial flowers, never should follow nature.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000342","text":"Manufacturers of both articles perfectly understand this; and hence the superiority of their productions to the mere realities that flutter and bloom for their brief hour, and then die.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000343","text":"There is nothing in entomology so beautiful as a well-busked trout or salmon fly.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beauty","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000344","text":"And then it is comparatively indestructible.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000345","text":"Take a natural May Fly and squeeze it in your hand.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000346","text":"Try the same experiment with an artificial one, and its plumage remains unruffled—which is more than you do, since the chance is that you will have to employ a surgeon to extract the hook from the ball of your thumb.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000347","text":"We are assured by a broker, who, in Spring-time, always becomes a brooker, that by far the surest lure for a large trout is the Greenback Fly.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000348","text":"He is acquainted with a man who, whenever he goes a-fishing, always has a four-pound trout to pack in ice and send up to a friend in the city.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000349","text":"By post, a letter is dispatched to the same quarter, containing a warm description of the playing and landing of that noble fish.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000350","text":"The sender usually states that he captured it with the famous fly known to anglers as the Green Drake.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000351","text":"Facts are against him, though; and it is well understood by his friends that the fish was first taken by some poaching rascal with a scoop-net, and subsequently hooked by the angler with a five-dollar Greenback Fly.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000352","text":"Nothing in life is more beautiful than a five-dollar Greenback Fly—except, of course, a ten-dollar one, or one of indefinitely larger denomination.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:beauty","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000353","text":"Provided with this most charming and effective of lures, the angler is always sure to fill his creel.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000354","text":"_How to make the Greenback Fly_—Give it to your wife.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000355","text":"Much has been said concerning the efficacy of the Water Fly as a lure.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000356","text":"We know rather less about it than we do about the Water Cure; but we cheerfully print the following directions on the subject, taken from the fly-leaf of an old book.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000357","text":"_How to make the Water Fly_: Fall into it.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000358","text":"HAYKS and those of Captain HALL are engaged in a heated discussion as to which of the two ought to be sent by Congress in search of the North Pole.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000359","text":"As the public does not know who is right and who is wrong, we present our readers with the arguments of each party; so that they can decide which explorer is the man for the post—we should say, pole.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:creativity","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000360","text":"1. The Pole being surrounded by water, must be reached by boats. HAYES is a sailor and HALL is not. Therefore HAYES is the man to sail to the Pole.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000361","text":"2. HAYES is a Bostonian; HALL is a Western man. Bostonians are famed for their skill in prying into every thing; while Western men stupidly mind their own business. Therefore HAYES is naturally fitted to become an explorer.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000362","text":"3. HALL spent his time while in the Arctic Region in the society of Esquimaux. HAYES attended to his ship, and lived on pork and beef like a Christian. Therefore HAYES is the better man.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:christianity","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000363","text":"4. HAYES understands the use of instruments, and can take observations of the temperature of hot springs, if any are found. HALL knows nothing about instruments, and could not tell the time by a barometer if his life depended upon it. Therefore HAYES should be the Congressional favorite.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000364","text":"5. HALL is hot-tempered and once killed one of his crew. HAYES is a cool man and never killed any body, except as a medical practitioner. Cool men are at home in the Arctic Region. Therefore send HAYES.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000365","text":"1. If the Pole is surrounded by water, it must be a visible point of land. HALL is a landsman, and therefore the proper man to send in search of land. To send a sailor like HAYES in quest of land would be absurd. Therefore HALL is the right man.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000366","text":"2. HALL is a steady, hardworking, energetic Western man. HAYES is a meddling Yankee. Of course HALL is the better man for carrying out a difficult enterprise.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000367","text":"3. HALL has lived in the Arctic land as the Arctic people do; while HAYES knows nothing of the people of that region. Therefore HALL is by far the best man to send.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000368","text":"HAYES can have no use for his instruments in a place where there is nothing but ice.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000369","text":"HAYES would, therefore, only add to the cost of the expedition.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000370","text":"HALL can take all necessary observations with his eyes, which cost Congress nothing and are easily carried.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000371","text":"Therefore HALL is by all odds the man for the expedition.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000372","text":"If HALL is hot-tempered, so much the better.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000373","text":"He will keep warm with less consumption of fuel.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000374","text":"That he killed a mutineer is proof of his resolute adherence to discipline.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000375","text":"HAYES would never enforce discipline if he dared to inflict no more punishment for mutiny than a draught of Epsom salts.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:courage","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000376","text":"Therefore HALL is plainly the man to command an exploring party.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000377","text":"Here we have the arguments which both sides advance, and our readers can easily make up their minds.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000378","text":"As for ourselves, the true course for Congress to pursue seems so plainly evident that if we were asked which is the best man, the Doctor or the Captain, we should unhesitatingly answer in the negative.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000379","text":"(Adapted from AUTHOR'S Classical Dictionary, p. 351.)","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000380","text":"\"CINCINNATUS had retired to his patrimony, aloof from popular tumults.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000381","text":"The successes of the Equi, (young Democracy,) however, rendered the appointment of a Dictator necessary, and CINCINNATUS was chosen to that high office.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000382","text":"He laid aside his rural habiliments, assumed the ensigns of absolute power, levied a new army, marched all night to bring the necessary succor to the Consul MINCIUS, (W.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000383","text":"TWEED,) who was surrounded by the enemy and blockaded in his camp, (Albany,) and before morning surrounded the enemy's army, and reduced it to a condition exactly similar to that in which the Romans had been placed.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000384","text":"The baffled Equi were glad to submit to the victor's terms, and CINCINNATUS, returning in, triumph to Rome, (New-York,) laid down his dictatorial power after having held it only fourteen days, and returned to his farm\" (Central Park.)","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000385","text":"In such a joyous way? If it were as you say, Wouldn't _I_ know it, who know every thing!","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000386","text":"\"Ethereal mildness!\" Pshaw! what nonsense, man! Pooh! \"Gentle spring,\" indeed! It makes my liver bleed To hear you talk as only idiots can.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000387","text":"But you're no idiot, THOMSON; _that_ I'll say! I'll yield another bit: I'm ready to admit The Seasons may have altered since your day.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000388","text":"At any rate, JAMES, in the windy West (Which wasn't in your eye— At least, not frequently) Your boasted Spring is _not_ a gentle guest.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000389","text":"My patience, no! She's the reverse of that! Ah! hear her savage roar; (So often heard before!) And there (confound it!) goes my new Spring hat.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000390","text":"Alas! what means this stupid somnolence? Why do my pulses go So \"melancholy slow\"? Why can't I think? why always \"on the fence\"?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000391","text":"O dews and fogs! O rain and snow and slush! O various other things! My soul! what need of wings: Yes, \"Spring's delights\" are coming with a rush!","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000392","text":"But stay, friend THOMSON—what you say is true: Here _is_ a nice warm day! The breezes softly play— Then why, oh! _why_ then, do I feel so blue?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000393","text":"One \"would not die in Spring-time,\" certainly— Nor any other season, For the same reason— But if one can't eat dinner, why _not_ die?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000394","text":"Is there no panacea for such ills? Oh! yes, a jolly one: I find it in the dun! In landlords', butchers', grocers', tailors' bills!","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:christianity","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000395","text":"GOLDEN calves were worshipped by men of old. Modern men prefer to worship saw-dust calves.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000396","text":"Is Canada to be the Theatre of a Fenian War? It seems that the Canadian Volunteers think so; and, to do justice to the performance, they have taken possession of the whole Front-tier.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:justice","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000397","text":"[Illustration: THE SICK EAGLE COLUMBIA. “DO LET THE POOR BIRD OUT, MR. B.; HE DROOPS SADLY.” Mr. BOOTWELL. “REALLY I DON’T SEE ANY THING THE MATTER WITH HIM, MA’AM. HIS CAGE IS ALL GOLD, AND HE SURELY OUGHT TO BE CONTENTED.”]","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000398","text":"Is there for his dishonesty Who hangs his head, and a' that? The coward slave, we pass him by, And dare to steal for a' that. For a' that and a' that, Our grabs and games, and a' that, Our business is to make a pile And swindle SAM, and a' that.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:courage","theme:love","theme:truth","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000399","text":"What though the people curse and swear At losing gold, and a' that? Their fiercest wrath we'll proudly bear, And cash is cash for a' that. For a' that and a' that, Their lawyers, courts, and a' that. The lucky rogue who wins his pile Is king of men for a' that.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000400","text":"The President knows how to beat In battle, siege, and a' that; But we're the lads for swift retreat, Although he growl, and a' that. For a' that and a' that, Our bonds and oaths and a' that, A bouncing swag's the better thing For gentlemen, and a' that.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:relationships","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000401","text":"Then let us pray that come it may, As come it shall for a' that, That plundering gents may keep the sway, And help themselves, and a' that. For a' that and a' that. Leg bail's the thing, and a' that; For travelling improves the mind, The body saves, and a' that.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000402","text":"The New-York omnibus was constructed to seat and carry twelve persons; certainly not more.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000403","text":"Indeed, when twelve men, of nominal size, sit squarely on the seats and do not clownishly cross their legs, one may ride in an omnibus with comfort.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000404","text":"Nay, with these conditions, he _may_ generally escape having his toes crushed, his shins kicked, his shoes soiled, or his trowsers daubed with mud by his neighbor.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000405","text":"how often is this paradisiacal state disturbed by the intrusion of \"the thirteenth man in the omnibus.\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000406","text":"Shall I attempt to portray the creature?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000407","text":"He is pretty well known, and perhaps the picture will be recognized.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000408","text":"Sometimes he may be seen standing at the corner of the street lying in wait for the \"bus.\" He is never known to walk toward its starting-place, lest he might be confounded with the \"twelve\" by getting inside before the seats are filled.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000409","text":"His very hat never sits squarely upon his head like the hat of a gentleman.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000410","text":"It is either elevated in front like a sophomore's, or depressed on one side, as if he had just come from a cheap spree in the Bowery, or was troubled with some obtrusive \"bump\" that kept his hat awry.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000411","text":"If by chance he gets a seat inside the omnibus, (as \"accidents will happen,\" etc.,) he must cross his legs and wipe the mud from his ill-shod feet upon your trowsers or your wife's dress.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000412","text":"Indeed, methinks it was he who invented sitting cross-legged in a public vehicle.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000413","text":"Do savages ever sit thus when in close company?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000414","text":"I have never been able to imagine what special human sin this ingenious mode of annoyance was meant to punish.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000415","text":"It has been suggested that it might be the man's pantomimic protest against sitting at all.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000416","text":"But the saddest commentary upon this vice of our hero is, that by some mysterious magnetism of awkwardness and ill-breeding, he has betrayed into imitation of it men whose early education has been less neglected than his own.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000417","text":"Sometimes, as he gets into the \"'bus,\" he carries in his hand or mouth the stump of a half-burned, extinct cigar, which fills the atmosphere with a rank and sickening odor.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000418","text":"More frequently he is dressed in well-worn black, and his clothes reek with noisome exhalations of stale tobacco-smoke.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000419","text":"I verily believe he is the original Loafer.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000420","text":"I have just handed up my fare, and, taking my seat, have surrendered myself to a sweet half-hour of reverie.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000421","text":"I disdain to spoil my eyes or waste my time by newspaper-reading.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000422","text":"I dream, and save my time for better things, as I conceive.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000423","text":"\"Twelve inside.\" The driver does not seem to get along.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000424","text":"He is constantly stopping or turning his horses to the sidewalk, right or left.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000425","text":"You begin to think the whole town is striving to get a ride down with you in that particular \"'bus.\" At every street-corner we linger or stop.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:action","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000426","text":"Suddenly the door is pulled open with a jerk and our enemy leaps in.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000427","text":"He sees the seats are filled, but he does not hesitate.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000428","text":"Indeed, his \"spirit rises with the occasion.\" He becomes pertinacious as he is offensive.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:animism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000429","text":"He tramples upon more than one pair of feet in his struggle to reach the middle of the omnibus.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000430","text":"The passengers patiently submit to the intrusion with that quiet good nature with which Americans usually suffer imposition invasive of good manners, or petty social rights.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:justice","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000431","text":"They seem to feel they can \"stand it\" if he can.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000432","text":"His mode of paying his fare evolves a climax of unconscious impertinence.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000433","text":"In order to have free use of one hand to pass up his money, he grasps cane or umbrella with the other hand, by which he holds the pendent strap.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000434","text":"By this means he loses control of the lower end of his stick, which thereby becomes an automatic instrument of torture, menacing your face and eyes in quite a savage way.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000435","text":"Indeed, his apparent unconsciousness that he is a nuisance, and ought to be kicked out, really approaches the sublime.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:beauty","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000436","text":"Some innocent people wonder that the drivers of omnibuses or cars should feel so very charitably disposed toward the human family in general, as to take up extra passengers when all seats are filled.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beauty","theme:love","theme:nature","theme:relationships","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000437","text":"The more passengers, beyond the complement of the \"'bus,\" the more perquisites for an ill-requited profession.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000438","text":"As he grows weary, he grasps the straps on either side to steady him.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000439","text":"His attitude is a cunningly devised mode of tormenting his fellow-passengers.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000440","text":"Either elbow of our nondescript just reaches the hat of your opposite neighbor or yourself.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000441","text":"With each jolt of the stage, by a little dexterity of movement, or want of it, he can knock the hats over the eyes of two persons at a time, and by a little shifting of his position he can frequently bring down four by a single spasmodic lunge.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000442","text":"When he is fresher, as in the morning, and can hold his own weight, he falls in his more natural posture.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000443","text":"Did you ever observe one of the descendants of the Lost Tribes who inhabit Chatham street dreamily waiting for a passing rustic?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000444","text":"His abdomen is drawn in; his body is bent like a section of a hoop; his eyes are cast down; while both his hands are thrust deeply into his trowser's pockets.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000445","text":"But I grow weary of the subject, and stop by commending the Thirteenth Man in the Omnibus to curiosity-hunters as a fungus growth of humanity nursed by over-virtuous forbearance.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000446","text":"The hyperbole of bores it is, to bore Congress for a hundred thousand dollars to go to the Pole!","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000447","text":"If Captain HALL wants adventure, let him travel to the Halls of the MONTEZUMAS.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000448","text":"If he wishes only to be left out in the cold, let him go to Chili; or else up in a balloon; or let him make himself Republican candidate for something in New York.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000449","text":"We believe the North Pole would rather be let alone.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000450","text":"The whole subject is, at all events, too HAYES-y just now to be comprehended.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000451","text":"There is a sort of KANE-ine madness, which shows itself not in fear of water but in an insane disposition to do big things on ice.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000452","text":"Is a temperance lecture synonymous with a Water Spout?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000453","text":"PUNCHINELLO: According to your instructions, your correspondent proceeded to Washington, and there interviewed our present efficient Secretary of the Navy, Admiral PORTER.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000454","text":"I found him in his office, surrounded by bills-of-sale of main-tops, carronades, iron-clads, bo'sen's whistles, navy-yards, and other naval articles, the proceeds of which were needed for the future experiments of the Department.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000455","text":"These papers were being bound up into bundles and stowed away by his assistant, ROBESON.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000456","text":"After the ordinary greetings had passed between the admiral and your correspondent, the following conversation ensued:","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000457","text":"_Cor_. Admiral, what do you think of the Fifteenth Amendment?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000458","text":"_Ad_. All right. When Americans want votes, I say, give 'em to 'em.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000459","text":"_Cor_, (_A little apprehensively._) Votes are different from boats, then, admiral?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000460","text":"_Ad_. Certainly. What do the negroes want with boats?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000461","text":"_Cor_. How are you satisfied, Mr. Secretary, with the plan of always providing you with a civilian as an assistant?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000462","text":"_Ad_. I don't like it. Can't help it, though. This one, however, (_pointing his thumb over his shoulder at_ ROBESON,) don't give me much trouble. Quiet man.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000463","text":"_Cor_. What do you think of the condition of Cuba,","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000464","text":"_Ad_. Very nice indeed! Got Admiral POOR out there, cruising around. Just like a picnic, you know.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000465","text":"_Cor_. Are you in favor of the recognition of Cuban Independence?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000466","text":"_Ad_. No, sir! What's the good? POOR might have to come home, then.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000467","text":"_Cor_. You think, then, that recognition would not be a Poor policy?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000468","text":"_Ad_. Yes—no! No—yes! Doormat! You know what I mean.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000469","text":"_Cor_.(_quickly_.) Oh! yes. Certainly,sir! But what is your opinion upon the woman question?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000470","text":"_Ad_. Don't care a snap. Let 'em vote. Won't make a difference 'board ship.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000471","text":"_Cor_. You think, then that women will never be sailors, Admiral?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000472","text":"_Ad_. Nothing they could do. Except to trim the boats; look out for the mizen sheets or somethg o' that kind. Couldn't expect 'em, even in a calm, to be brisk in manning the yards, much less martingales.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000473","text":"_Cor_. What is your opinion, Admiral, of SHERIDAN'S work among the Piegans?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000474","text":"_Ad_. (_laughing_). Neat job. How was that for Lo?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000475","text":"_Cor_. Good. Do you believe the Pope's infallible, Admiral?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000476","text":"_Cor_. Do you think that there is no such word as fail with PIO Nono?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000477","text":"_Cor_. The Empress EUGENIE, Admiral, and Queen VICTORIA—which do you think is the prettiest of these women?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000478","text":"_Ad_. Never saw 'em swimmin'. Can't say.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000479","text":"_Cor_. What is your opinion about McFARLAND? Was he justifiable, think you?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000480","text":"_Cor_. Have you seen _Frou Frou_, Admiral?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000481","text":"_Ad_. Not much. Do for folks whose taste for that sort of thing is DAILY bred.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000482","text":"_Cor_. What do you think of oar new City Charter?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000483","text":"_Cor_. Yes, sir. It is a sort of hardship for New-York.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000484","text":"_Ad_. Well, the city must be used to that. Will take in its ale pretty much as usual, I reckon.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000485","text":"_Cor_. What, sir, do you think of Chicago?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000486","text":"_Cor_. (_oblivious of hint_.) Where do you buy your pantaloon stuff, Mr. Secretary?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000487","text":"_Ad_. (_sharply_.) Where the woodbine twineth.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000488","text":"_Cor_. My dear sir, you surprise me! Is he your son?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000489","text":"_Ad_. (_to assistant_.) ROBESON! Did you see MIKE HAINES?","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000490","text":"_Cor_. One moment. Admiral! Let me ask of you, in which, if any, of our New-York companies is your life insured; and do you wear the patent perforated buckskin?—","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000491","text":"Here the interview terminated. Your correspondent suddenly discovered that he would have barely time to catch the N. Y. Express, and he took leave with a renewed respect for the spirit of our Navy and its head.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:animism","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000492","text":"Now is the time to ask your friends for seed and roots, and to tell somebody they ought to see about the garden.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000493","text":"Turn your chickens into your neighbors' grounds, and the cow too, if you think she would like to go there.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000494","text":"Now also is the time for house-cleaning, as well as for settling up one's affairs generally; so, after you have called in all the money due you, and paid out as little as possible, perhaps you had better go out West for a week or so.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:justice","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000495","text":"The sort of Liquor most apt to Tell upon a Man.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000496","text":"The _Sun_ thinks that the World's end would be a god-send.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000497","text":"It also thinks that the Tribune is a try weakly and unique daily, besides being a four centenary.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000498","text":"It thinks that the fact of the _Times_ being out of Joint is the reason it is getting the cold Shoulder from its subscribers.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000499","text":"It thinks that the _Herald_ is not the leading paper, though it may have Ben-it.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000500","text":"It thinks that the _Sun_ is awful shiny.","author":"Saadi","source":"Gulistan — Gladwin Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000501","text":"Produced by Steven Gibbs, William Flis, and the Online Distributed Proofreading Team.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000502","text":"LIEUT.-GEN. SIR ROBERT BADEN-POWELL, K.C.B.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000503","text":"_Illustrated by the Author's Own Sketches_","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000504","text":"A Handbook for Instruction in Good Citizenship. 7th Edition. The Official Handbook of the Boy Scouts.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000505","text":"\"There is no gift book that could be put into the hands of a schoolboy more valuable than this fascinating volume, and if you asked the boy's opinion he would probably add, 'No book that he liked better.'\"--_Spectator_.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000506","text":"A splendid collection of Outdoor and Indoor Games specially compiled for the use of Boy Scouts. 2nd Edition.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000507","text":"\"My World Tour.\" Illustrated by the Author's own Sketches.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000508","text":"\"Describes in brightest and most concise fashion his recent tour of inspection amongst the Boy Scouts.... Every boy will read it with avidity and pronounce it 'jolly good.'\"--_Graphic_.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000509","text":"_Price 1/- each in Pictorial Wrapper, or 2/- each in Cloth Boards. Postage 3d. extra._","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000510","text":"It has been difficult to write in peace-time on the delicate subject of spies and spying, but now that the war is in progress and the methods of those much abused gentry have been disclosed, there is no harm in going more fully into the question, and to relate some of my own personal experiences.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000511","text":"Spies are like ghosts--people seem to have had a general feeling that there might be such things, but they did not at the same time believe in them--because they never saw them, and seldom met anyone who had had first-hand experience of them.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000512","text":"But as regards the spies, I can speak with personal knowledge in saying that they do exist, and in very large numbers, not only in England, but in every part of Europe.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:creativity","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000513","text":"As in the case of ghosts, any phenomenon which people don't understand, from a sudden crash on a quiet day to a midnight creak of a cupboard, has an affect of alarm upon nervous minds. So also a spy is spoken of with undue alarm and abhorrence, because he is somewhat of a bogey.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000514","text":"As a first step it is well to disabuse one's mind of the idea that every spy is necessarily the base and despicable fellow he is generally held to be. He is often both clever and brave.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:courage","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000515","text":"The term \"spy\" is used rather indiscriminately, and has by use come to be a term of contempt.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000516","text":"As a misapplication of the term \"spy\" the case of Major André always seems to me to have been rather a hard one.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000517","text":"He was a Swiss by birth, and during the American War of Independence in 1780 joined the British Army in Canada, where he ultimately became A.D.C.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000518","text":"The American commander of a fort near West Point, on the Hudson River, had hinted that he wanted to surrender, and Sir H.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000519","text":"In order to get through the American lines André dressed himself in plain clothes and took the name of John Anderson.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000520","text":"He was unfortunately caught by the Americans and tried by court martial and hanged as a spy.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000521","text":"As he was not trying to get information, it seems scarcely right to call him a spy. Many people took this view at the time, and George III. gave his mother a pension, as well as a title to his brother, and his body was ultimately dug up and re-interred in Westminster Abbey.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000522","text":"Let us for the moment change the term \"spy\" to \"investigator\" or \"military agent.\" For war purposes these agents may be divided into:","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000523","text":"_Strategical_ and diplomatic _agents_, who study the political and military conditions in peace time of all other countries which might eventually be in opposition to their own in war.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000524","text":"2. _Tactical_, military, or naval _agents_, who look into minor details of armament and terrain in peace time. These also make tactical preparations on the spot, such as material for extra bridges, gun emplacements, interruption of communications, etc.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000525","text":"3. _Field spies_. Those who act as scouts in disguise to reconnoitre positions and to report moves of the enemy in the field of war. Amongst these are residential spies and officer agents.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000526","text":"All these duties are again subdivided among agents of every grade, from ambassadors and their attachés downwards. Naval and military officers are sent to carry out special investigations by all countries, and paid detectives are stationed in likely centres to gather information.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000527","text":"There are also traitor spies. For these I allow I have not a good word. They are men who sell their countries' secrets for money. Fortunately we are not much troubled with them in England; but we have had a notorious example in South Africa.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000528","text":"The war treason--that is, preliminary political and strategical investigation--of the Germans in the present campaign has not been such a success as might have been expected from a scheme so wonderfully organised as it has been.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:beauty","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000529","text":"With the vast sums spent upon it, the German General Staff might reasonably have obtained men in a higher position in life who could have gauged the political atmosphere better than was done by their agents immediately before the present crisis.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000530","text":"Their plans for starting strikes at a critical time met with no response whatever.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000531","text":"They had great ideas of stirring up strife and discontent among the Mahommedan populations both in Egypt and in India, but they calculated without knowing enough of the Eastern races or their feelings towards Great Britain and Germany--more especially Germany.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000532","text":"They looked upon the Irish question as being a certainty for civil war in Britain, and one which would necessitate the employment of a large proportion of our expeditionary force within our own islands.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000533","text":"All this might have been discovered if the Germans had employed men of a higher education and social position.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000534","text":"The Germans in the present war have been using the huge guns whose shells, owing to their black, smoky explosions, have been nicknamed \"Black Marias\" or \"Jack Johnsons.\" These guns require strong concrete foundations for them to stand upon before they can be fired.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000535","text":"But the Germans foresaw this long before the war, and laid their plans accordingly.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000536","text":"They examined all the country over which they were likely to fight, both in Belgium and in France, and wherever they saw good positions for guns they built foundations and emplacements for them.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000537","text":"This was done in the time of peace, and therefore had to be done secretly.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000538","text":"In order to divert suspicion, a German would buy or rent a farm on which it was desired to build an emplacement.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000539","text":"Then he would put down foundations for a new barn or farm building, or--if near a town--for a factory, and when these were complete, he would erect some lightly constructed building upon it.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000540","text":"There was nothing to attract attention or suspicion about this, and numbers of these emplacements are said to have been made before war began. When war broke out and the troops arrived on the ground, the buildings were hastily pulled down and there were the emplacements all ready for the guns.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000541","text":"Some years ago a report came to the War Office that a foreign Power was making gun emplacements in a position which had not before been suspected of being of military value, and they were evidently going to use it for strategical purposes.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000542","text":"I was sent to see whether the report was true.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000543","text":"Of course, it would not do to go as an officer--suspicions would be aroused, one would be allowed to see nothing, and would probably be arrested as a spy.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000544","text":"I therefore went to stay with a friendly farmer in the neighbourhood, and went out shooting every day among the partridges and snipe which abounded there.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000545","text":"The first thing I did was to look at the country generally, and try to think which points would be most valuable as positions for artillery.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000546","text":"Then I went to look for partridges (and other things!) on the hills which I had noticed, and I very soon found what I wanted.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000547","text":"Officers were there, taking angles and measurements, accompanied by workmen, who were driving pegs into the ground and marking off lines with tapes between them.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000548","text":"As I passed with my gun in my hand, bag on shoulder, and dog at heel, they paid no attention to me, and from the neighbouring hills I was able to watch their proceedings.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000549","text":"So that within a few days of their starting to make them we had the plans of them all in our possession.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000550","text":"Although they afterwards planted trees all over the sites to conceal the forts within them, and put up buildings in other places to hide them, we knew perfectly well where the emplacements were and what were their shapes and sizes.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000551","text":"This planting of trees to hide such defence works occasionally has the other effect, and shows one where they are.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000552","text":"This was notably the case at Tsingtau, captured by the Japanese and British forces from the Germans.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000553","text":"As there were not any natural woods there, I had little difficulty in finding where the forts were by reason of the plantations of recent growth in the neighbourhood of the place.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000554","text":"These men take up their quarters more or less permanently in the country of their operations.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000555","text":"A few are men in high places in the social or commercial world, and are generally _nouveaux riches_, anxious for decorations and rewards.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000556","text":"But most of the residential spies are of a more insignificant class, and in regular pay for their work.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000557","text":"Their duty is to act as agents to receive and distribute instructions secretly to other itinerant spies, and to return their reports to headquarters.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000558","text":"For this reason they are nicknamed in the German Intelligence Bureau \"post-boxes.\" They also themselves pick up what information they can from all available sources and transmit it home.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000559","text":"One, Steinbauer, has for some years past been one of the principal \"post-boxes\" in England. He was attached to the Kaiser's staff during his last visit to this country, when he came as the guest of the King to the opening of Queen Victoria's memorial.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000560","text":"A case of espionage which was tried in London revealed his methods, one of his agents being arrested after having been watched for three years.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000561","text":"Karl Ernst's trial confirmed the discoveries and showed up the doings of men spies like Schroeder, Gressa, Klare, and others.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000562","text":"Karl Graves may be still in the memory of many.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000563","text":"This German was arrested in Scotland for spying, and was condemned to eighteen months' imprisonment, and was shortly afterwards released without any reason being officially assigned.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000564","text":"He has since written a full account of what he did, and it is of interest to note how his correspondence passed to and from the intelligence headquarters in Germany in envelopes embellished with the name of Messrs.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000565","text":"Burroughs and Wellcome, the famous chemists.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000566","text":"He posed as a doctor, and sent his letters through an innkeeper at Brussels or a _modiste_ in Paris, while letters to him came through an obscure tobacconist's shop in London.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000567","text":"One of these letters miscarried through having the wrong initial to his name.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000568","text":"It was returned by the Post Office to Burroughs and Wellcome, who on opening it found inside a German letter, enclosing bank-notes in return for services rendered.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000569","text":"He states that a feeling that he was being followed dawned upon him one day, when he noticed in his lodgings that the clothes which he had folded on a chair had been since refolded in a slightly different way while he was out.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000570","text":"With some suspicion, he asked his landlady whether anyone had entered his room, and she, in evident confusion, denied that any stranger could have been there.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000571","text":"Then he suggested that his tailor might have called, and she agreed that it was so.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000572","text":"But when an hour or two later he interviewed his tailor, he, on his part, said he had not been near the place.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000573","text":"Graves consequently deduced that he was being followed.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000574","text":"The knowledge that you are being watched, and you don't know by whom, gives, I can assure you, a very jumpy feeling--especially when you know you are guilty.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000575","text":"I can speak feelingly from more than one experience of it, since I have myself been employed on this form of scouting in peace time.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000576","text":"It is generally difficult to find ordinary spies who are also sufficiently imbued with technical knowledge to be of use in gaining naval or military details. Consequently officers are often employed to obtain such information in peace time as well as in the theatre of action in war.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000577","text":"But with them, and especially with those of Germany, it is not easy to find men who are sufficiently good actors, or who can disguise their appearance so well as to evade suspicion.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000578","text":"Very many of these have visited our shores during the past few years, but they have generally been noticed, watched, and followed, and from the line taken by them in their reconnaissance it has been easy to deduce the kind of operations contemplated in their plans.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000579","text":"I remember the case of a party of these motoring through Kent nominally looking at old Roman ruins.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000580","text":"When they asked a landowner for the exact position of some of these he regretted he had not a map handy on which he could point out their position.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000581","text":"One of the \"antiquarians\" at once produced a large scale map; but it was not an English map: it had, for instance, details on it regarding water supply tanks which, though they existed, were not shown on any of our ordnance maps!","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000582","text":"In addition to the various branches of spying which I have mentioned, the Germans have also practised commercial espionage on systematic lines.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000583","text":"Young Germans have been often known to serve in British business houses without salary in order to \"learn the language\"; they took care to learn a good deal more than the language, and picked up many other things about trade methods and secrets which were promptly utilised in their own country.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000584","text":"The importance of commercial spying is that commercial war is all the time at the bottom of Germany's preparations for military war.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000585","text":"Carl Lody, a German ex-officer, was recently tried in London by court-martial and shot for \"war treason\"--that is, for sending information regarding our Navy to Germany during hostilities.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000586","text":"(\"War treason\" is secret work outside the zone of war operations.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000587","text":"When carried on within the zone of operations it is called spying or \"espionage.\") Carl Lody's moves were watched and his correspondence opened by the counter-spy police in London, and thus all his investigations and information were known to the War Office long before he was arrested.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000588","text":"The enormous sums paid by Germany for many years past have brought about a sort of international spy exchange, generally formed of American-Germans, with their headquarters in Belgium, and good prices were given for information acquired by them.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000589","text":"For instance, if the plans of a new fort, or the dimensions of a new ship, or the power of a new gun were needed, one merely had to apply and state a price to this bureau to receive fairly good information on the subject before much time had elapsed.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:justice","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000590","text":"At the same time, by pretending to be an American, one was able to get a good deal of minor and useful information without the expenditure of a cent.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000591","text":"On getting into touch with these gentry, I was informed of one of the intended plans by which the Germans proposed to invade our country, and incidentally it throws some light on their present methods of dealing with the inhabitants as apart from the actual tactical movements of the troops.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:creativity","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000592","text":"The German idea then--some six years ago--was that they could, by means of mines and submarines, at any time block the traffic in the British Channel in the space of a few hours, thus holding our home fleets in their stations at Spithead and Portland.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000593","text":"With the Straits of Dover so blocked, they could then rush a fleet of transports across the North Sea from Germany, to the East Coast of England, either East Anglia or, as in this plan, in Yorkshire.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000594","text":"They had in Germany nine embarking stations, with piers and platforms, all ready made, and steel lighters for disembarkation purposes or for actual traversing of the ocean in case of fine weather.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000595","text":"They had taken the average of the weather for years past, and had come to the conclusion that July 13th is, on an average, the finest day in the year; but their attempt would be timed, if possible, to fall on a Bank Holiday when communications were temporarily disorganised.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000596","text":"Therefore the nearest Bank Holiday to July 13th would probably be that at the beginning of August; it was a coincidence that the present war broke out on that day.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000597","text":"The spies stationed in England were to cut all telephone and telegraph wires, and, where possible, to blow down important bridges and tunnels, and thus to interrupt communications and create confusion.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000598","text":"Their idea of landing on the coast of Yorkshire was based on the following reasons:--","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000599","text":"Bringing a week's provisions with them, and seizing all the local provisions, they would have enough to sustain them for a considerable time, and the first step of their occupation would be to expel every inhabitant--man, woman, and child--from the neighbourhood and destroy the towns.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:leadership","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000600","text":"Thus, within a few hours, some fourteen millions of people would be starving, and wandering without shelter over the face of the country--a disaster which would need a large force to deal with, and would cause entire disruption of our food supplies and of business in the country.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000601","text":"The East Coast of Yorkshire between the Humber and Scarborough lends itself to such an adventure, by providing a good open beach for miles, with open country in front of it, which, in its turn, is protected by a semi-circle of wolds, which could be easily held by the German covering force.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000602","text":"Its left would be protected by the Humber and the right by the Tees, so that the landing could be carried out without interruption.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000603","text":"That was their plan--based on careful investigation by a small army of spies--some five or six years ago, before our naval bases had been established in the north.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000604","text":"If they had declared war then, they, might have had no serious interference from our Navy during the passage of their transports, which, of course, would be protected on that flank by their entire fleet of warships.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000605","text":"At first glance, it seems too fanciful a plan to commend itself to belief, but in talking it over with German officers, I found they fully believed in it as a practical proposition.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000606","text":"They themselves enlarged on the idea of the use that they would thus make of the civil population, and foreshadowed their present brutality by explaining that when war came, it would not be made with kid gloves.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000607","text":"The meaning of their commands would be brought home to the people by shooting down civilians if necessary, in order to prove that they were in earnest, and to force the inhabitants through terror to comply with their requirements.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000608","text":"Further investigations on the subject proved that the embarkation arrangements were all planned and prepared for.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000609","text":"At any time in the ordinary way of commerce there were numerous large mail steamers always available in their ports to transport numbers even largely in excess of those that would be assembled for such an expedition.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000610","text":"Troops could be mobilised in the neighbourhood of the ports, ostensibly for manoeuvres, without suspicion being aroused.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000611","text":"It is laid down in German strategical textbooks that the time for making war is not when you have a political cause for it, but when your troops are ready and the enemy is unready; and that to strike the first blow is the best way to declare war.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000612","text":"\"You are but a brown-paper general,\" said one, \"and if you think that by your foolish talk you are to frighten us from coming, you are not right.\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000613","text":"It is difficult to say where exactly a spy's work ends in war, and that of a scout begins, except that, as a rule, the first is carried out in disguise.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000614","text":"The scout is looked up to as a brave man, and his expedients for gaining information are thought wonderfully clever, so long as he remains in uniform.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beauty","theme:courage","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000615","text":"If he goes a bit further, and finds that he can get his information better by adopting a disguise--even at the greater risk to himself through the certainty of being shot if he is found out--then he is looked down upon as a \"despicable spy.\" I don't see the justice of it myself.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:justice","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000616","text":"A good spy--no matter which country he serves--is _of necessity_ a brave and valuable fellow.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:courage","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000617","text":"In our Army we do not make a very wide use of field spies on service, though their partial use at manoeuvres has shown what they can do.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000618","text":"In \"Aids to Scouting\" I have stated: \"In the matter of spying we are behind other nations. Spying, in reality, is reconnaissance in disguise. Its effects are so far-reaching that most nations, in order to deter enemies' spies, threaten them with death if caught.\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mortality","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000619","text":"As an essential part of scouting, I gave a chapter of hints on how to spy, and how to catch other people spying.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000620","text":"Spy-catching was once one of my duties, and is perhaps the best form of education towards successful spying.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000621","text":"I had been lucky enough to nail three and was complimented by one of the senior officers on the Commander-in-Chief's staff.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000622","text":"We were riding home together from a big review at the time that he was talking about it, and he remarked, \"How do you set about catching a spy?\" I told him of our methods and added that also luck very often came in and helped one.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000623","text":"Just in front of us, in the crowd of vehicles returning from the review-ground, was an open hired Victoria in which sat a foreign-looking gentleman.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000624","text":"I remarked that as an instance this was the sort of man I should keep an eye upon, and I should quietly follow him till I found where he lodged and then put a detective on to report his moves.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000625","text":"From our position on horseback close behind him we were able to see that our foreigner was reading a guide book and was studying a map of the fortifications through which we were passing.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:leadership","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000626","text":"Suddenly he called to the driver to stop for a moment while he lit a match for his cigarette.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000627","text":"The stranger glanced up to see that the man was not looking round, and then quickly slipped a camera from under the rug which was lying on the seat in front of him, and taking aim at the entrance shaft of a new ammunition store which had just been made for our Navy, he took a snapshot.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000628","text":"Then hurriedly covering up the camera again he proceeded to strike matches and to light his cigarette. Then he gave the word to drive on again.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000629","text":"We followed close behind till we came to where a policeman was regulating the traffic.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000630","text":"I rode ahead and gave him his instructions so that the carriage was stopped, and the man was asked to show his permit to take photographs.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000631","text":"The camera was taken into custody and the name and address of the owner taken \"with a view to further proceedings.\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000632","text":"Unfortunately at that time--it was many years ago--we were badly handicapped by our laws in the matter of arresting and punishing spies. By-laws allowed us to confiscate and smash unauthorised cameras, and that was all.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000633","text":"\"Further proceedings,\" had they been possible, in this case would have been unnecessary, for the suspected gentleman took himself off to the Continent by the very next boat.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000634","text":"But it took a good deal to persuade my staff-officer friend that the whole episode was not one faked up for his special edification.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000635","text":"Nobody could say that my native spy in South Africa, Jan Grootboom, was either a contemptible or mean kind of man. He was described by one who knew him as a \"white man in a black skin,\" and I heartily endorse the description.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000636","text":"Here is an instance of his work as a field spy:--","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000637","text":"Jan Grootboom was a Zulu by birth, but having lived much with white men, as a hunter and guide, he had taken to wearing ordinary clothes and spoke English perfectly well: but within him he had all the pluck and cunning of his race.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:leadership","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000638","text":"Now, every night was spent at this work--that is to say, the night was utilised for creeping to their positions, and one watched them during the day.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000639","text":"But it was impossible to do this without leaving footmarks and tracks, which the sharp eyes of their scouts were not slow to discover, and it very soon dawned upon them that they were being watched, and consequently they were continually on the look-out to waylay and capture us.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000640","text":"One night Grootboom and I had ridden to the neighbourhood of one of the enemy's camps, and were lying waiting for the early dawn before we could discover exactly where they were located.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000641","text":"It was during the hour before sunrise that, as a rule, the enemy used to light their fires for cooking their early morning food. One could thus see exactly their position, and could rectify one's own, so as to find a place where one could lie by during the day and watch their movements.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000642","text":"On this occasion the first fire was lit and then another sparkled up, and yet another, but before half a dozen had been lighted Grootboom suddenly growled under his breath:--","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000643","text":"\"The swine--they are laying a trap for us.\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000644","text":"I did not understand at the moment what he meant, but he said:--","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000645","text":"\"Stop here for a bit, and I will go and look.\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000646","text":"He slipped off all his clothing and left it lying in a heap, and stole away in the darkness, practically naked. Evidently he was going to visit them to see what was going on.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000647","text":"The worst of spying is that it makes you always suspicious, even of your best friends.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000648","text":"So, as soon as Grootboom was gone in one direction, I quietly crept away in another, and got among some rocks in a small kopje, where I should have some kind of a chance if he had any intention of betraying me and returning with a few Matabele to capture me.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000649","text":"For an hour or two I lay there, until presently I saw Grootboom creeping back through the grass--alone.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000650","text":"Ashamed of my doubts, I therefore came out and went to our rendezvous, and found him grinning all over with satisfaction while he was putting on his clothes again.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000651","text":"He said that he had found as he had expected, an ambush laid for us.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000652","text":"The thing that had made him suspicious was that the fires, instead of lighting up all over the hillside at different points about the same time, had been lighted in steady succession one after another, evidently by one man going round.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000653","text":"This struck him as suspicious, and he then assumed that it was done to lead us on, if we were anywhere around, to go and examine more closely the locality.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000654","text":"He had crept in towards them by a devious path, from which he was able to perceive a whole party of the Matabele lying low in the grass by the track which we should probably have used in getting there, and they would have pounced upon us and captured us.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000655","text":"To make sure of this suspicion he crept round till near their stronghold, and coming from there he got in among them and chatted away with them, finding out what was their intention with regard to ourselves, and also what were their plans for the near future.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000656","text":"Then, having left them, and walked boldly back towards their stronghold, he crept away amongst some rocks and rejoined me.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:courage","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000657","text":"His was an example of the work of a field spy which, although in a way it may be cunning and deceitful, at the same time demands the greatest personal courage and astuteness.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:courage","theme:love","theme:resilience","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000658","text":"It is something greater than the ordinary bravery of a soldier in action, who is carried on by the enthusiasm of those around him under the leadership of an officer, and with the competition and admiration of others.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:courage","theme:leadership","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000659","text":"The pluck of the man who goes out alone, unobserved and unapplauded, and at the risk of his life, is surely equally great.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000660","text":"The Boers used field spies freely against us in South Africa.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000661","text":"One English-speaking Boer used to boast how, during the war, he made frequent visits to Johannesburg dressed in the uniform taken from a British major who had been killed in action.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000662","text":"He used to ride past the sentries, who, instead of shooting him, merely saluted, and he frequented the clubs and other resorts of the officers, picking up such information as he required from them first hand, till evening came and he was able to ride back to his commando.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000663","text":"On our side various methods were adopted of conveying information in the field. My spies employed native runners (especially the most astute cattle-thieves) to take their despatches to me.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000664","text":"[Illustration: _These hieroglyphics contain a secret message which can be easily read by those who know the semaphore signalling code.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000665","text":"This signalling consists of swinging two arms in different positions, either singly or together.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000666","text":"The dots indicate where the letters join.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000667","text":"For example: The semaphore sign for N consists of both arms pointing downwards at an angle of 90 degrees ^.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000668","text":"The letter I is shown by both arms pointing to the left at the same angle >.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000669","text":"The next N is shown again, and the letter E is a single arm pointing upwards on the right at an angle of 45 degrees /._","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000670","text":"_In each word you start at the top of the signs and read downwards._","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:action","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000671","text":"_This form of secret message was frequently used in the South African War._]","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000672","text":"These were in every case naturally written in cypher or secret code, in Hindustani written in English characters, and so on.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000673","text":"They were rolled up into pellets and pressed into a small hole bored in a walking-stick, the hole being then plugged with clay or soap.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000674","text":"Or they were put into the bowl of a pipe underneath the tobacco, and could thus be burnt without suspicion if necessary, or they were slipped in between the soles of the boots, or stitched in the lining of the bearer's clothing.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000675","text":"These natives also understood the language of smoke-fires--signalling by means of little or big puffs of smoke as to the enemy's moves and strength.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:resilience","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000676","text":"The native despatch-runners whom we sent out to make their way through the enemy's lines carried the letters tightly rolled up in little balls, coated with sheet lead, such as tea is packed in.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000677","text":"These little balls they carried slung round their necks on a string. The moment that they saw an enemy coming near they dropped the balls, which then looked like so many stones, on the ground, and took bearings of the spot so that they could find them again when the coast was clear.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000678","text":"Then there were fixed points for hiding letters for other spies to find. Here are some of the most frequently used:","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000679","text":"[Illustration: _This little mark, scratched on the ground or on a tree trunk or gate-post, was used by one scout for the information of another. It means: \"A letter is hidden four paces in this direction.\"_","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000680","text":"[Illustration: _A sign used to warn another scout that he is following a wrong direction. It means: \"Not this way.\"_]","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000681","text":"[Illustration: _This is another sign from one scout to another and means: \"I have returned home.\"_]","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000682","text":"[Illustration: _The \"blaze\" on the tree trunk and the two stones, one on the other, are simply to show that the scout is on the right trail._","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000683","text":"_The other three sketches are to show the direction in which the scout should go.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000684","text":"The upper part of the sapling or bush is bent over in the direction which the scout should take, and the same is the case with the bunch of grass, which is first of all knotted and then bent._]","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000685","text":"The Japanese, of course, in their war with Russia in Manchuria made extensive use of spies, and Port Arthur, with all its defects of fortification and equipment, was known thoroughly inside and out to the Japanese general staff before they ever fired a shot at it.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000686","text":"The field spies are a recognised and efficient arm.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000687","text":"Frederick the Great is recorded to have said: \"When Marshal Subise goes to war, he is followed by a hundred cooks, but when I take the field I am preceded by a hundred spies.\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000688","text":"The present leader of the German army might well say the same, though probably his \"hundred\" would amount to thousands.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:leadership","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000689","text":"We hear of them dressed in plain clothes as peasants, and signalling with coloured lights, with puffs of smoke from chimneys, and by using the church clock hands as semaphores.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000690","text":"Very frequently a priest was arrested and found to be a spy disguised, and as such he was shot. Also a German chauffeur in a French uniform, who had for some time been driving French staff officers about, was found to be a spy, and so met his death.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mortality","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000691","text":"Early in the present war the German field spies had their secret code of signs, so that by drawing sketches of cattle of different colours and sizes on gates, etc., they conveyed information to each other of the strength and direction of different bodies of hostile troops in the neighbourhood.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","theme:resilience","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000692","text":"As a rule, these are residential spies, who have lived for months or years as small tradesmen, etc., in the towns and villages now included in the theatre of war.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000693","text":"On the arrival of the German invaders they have chalked on their doors, \"Not to be destroyed.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000694","text":"Good people here,\" and have done it for some of their neighbours also in order to divert suspicion.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000695","text":"In their capacity of naturalised inhabitants they are in position, of course, to gain valuable tactical information for the commanders of the troops.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000696","text":"And their different ways of communicating it are more than ingenious.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000697","text":"In some cases both spies and commanders have maps ruled off in small squares.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000698","text":"The watchful spy signals to his commander, \"Enemy's cavalry halted behind wood in square E15,\" and very soon a salvo of shells visits this spot.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000699","text":"A woman spy was caught signalling with an electric flash lamp.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000700","text":"Two different men (one of them an old one-legged stonebreaker at the roadside) were caught with field telephones hidden on them with wire coiled round their bodies.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000701","text":"Shepherds with lanterns went about on the downs at night dodging the lanterns about in various ways which did not seem altogether necessary for finding sheep.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000702","text":"Wireless telegraphs were set up to look like supports to iron chimneys.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000703","text":"In the South African Campaign a Dutch stationmaster acted as field spy for the Boers for a short time.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000704","text":"His town and station were captured by my force, and, in order to divert suspicion, he cut and pulled down the telegraph wires, all except one, which was left in working order.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000705","text":"By this wire he sent to the Boer headquarters all the information he could get about our forces and plans.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000706","text":"Unfortunately, we had a party of men tapping the wire, and were able to read all his messages, and to confront him with them shortly afterwards.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000707","text":"Another stationmaster, in our own territory, acted as spy to the enemy before the war began by employing enemies as gangers and platelayers along the line with a view to the destruction of bridges and culverts as soon as war was declared.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000708","text":"There was also found in his office a code by which the different arms of the service were designated in terms of timber for secretly telegraphing information.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000709","text":"Beams meant Brigades Timbers \" Batteries Logs \" Guns Scantlings \" Battalions Joists \" Squadrons Planks \" Companies","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000710","text":"Except in the case of the traitor spy, one does not quite understand why a spy should necessarily be treated worse than any other combatant, nor why his occupation should be looked upon as contemptible, for, whether in peace or war, his work is of a very exacting and dangerous kind.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000711","text":"It is intensely exciting, and though in some cases it brings a big reward, the best spies are unpaid men who are doing it for the love of the thing, and as a really effective step to gaining something valuable for their country and for their side.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000712","text":"The plea put forward by the German spy, Lieut.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000713","text":"Carl Lody, at his court-martial in London, was that \"he would not cringe for mercy.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000714","text":"He was not ashamed of anything that he had done; he was in honour bound not to give away the names of those who had employed him on this mission; he was not paid for it, he did it for his country's good, and he knew that he carried his life in his hands in doing so.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000715","text":"Many a Briton was probably doing the same for Britain.\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000716","text":"He was even spoken of in our House of Commons as being \"a patriot who had died for his country as much as any soldier who fell in the field.\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000717","text":"To be a really effective spy, a man has to be endowed with a strong spirit of self-sacrifice, courage, and self-control, with the power of acting a part, quick at observation and deduction, and blessed with good health and nerve of exceptional quality.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:grief-healing","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:courage","theme:creativity","theme:love","theme:mental-health","theme:resilience","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:animism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000718","text":"A certain amount of scientific training is of value where a man has to be able to take the angles of a fort, or to establish the geological formation, say, of the middle island under the Forth Bridge, which was shown by Graves to be readily adaptable for explosion purposes.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000719","text":"For anyone who is tired of life, the thrilling life of a spy should be the very finest recuperator!","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000720","text":"Quite another class of spy is the traitor who gives away the secrets of his own country.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000721","text":"Fortunately, the Briton is not as a rule of a corruptible character, and many foreign spies in England have been discovered through their attempts to bribe officers or men to give away secrets.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000722","text":"On the other hand, we hear frequently of foreign soldiers falling victims to such temptation, and eventually being discovered.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000723","text":"Cases have only recently come to light in Austria where officers were willing to sell information as regards a number of secret block-houses which were built on the frontier of Bukovina last year.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000724","text":"Details of them got into the hands of another Power within a few days of the designs being made.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000725","text":"Apparently when suspicion falls upon an officer in Austria the case is not tried in public, but is conducted privately, sometimes by the Emperor himself.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000726","text":"When the man is found guilty, the procedure is for four friends of the accused to visit him and tell him what has been discovered against him, and to present him with a loaded revolver and leave him.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000727","text":"They then remain watching the house, in order that he shall not escape, and until he elects to shoot himself; if he fails to do so, in reasonable time, they go in and finish him off between them.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000728","text":"The espionage system of the Germans far exceeds that of any other country in its extent, cost, and organisation.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000729","text":"It was thoroughly exposed after the war with France in 1870, when it was definitely shown that the German Government had an organisation of over 20,000 paid informers stationed in France, and controlled by one man, Stieber, for both political and military purposes.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000730","text":"Stieber himself was the valet, recommended to him as \"a thoroughly trustworthy servant.\" Stieber availed himself of his position to go through his master's pockets and despatch cases daily, collecting most valuable data and information for Bismarck.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:leadership","theme:love","theme:relationships","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000731","text":"Somehow, on the surface, suspicion of the German spy methods seemed to have subsided since that date, although at the time widely known throughout Europe.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000732","text":"But their methods have been steadily elaborated and carried into practice ever since, not in France alone, but in all the countries on the Continent, and also in Great Britain.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000733","text":"Fortunately for us, we are as a nation considered by the others to be abnormally stupid, therefore easily to be spied upon. But it is not always safe to judge entirely by appearances.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000734","text":"Our Ambassador at Constantinople some years ago had the appearance of a cheery, bluff, British farmer, with nothing below the surface in his character, and he was therefore looked upon as fair game by all his intriguing rivals in Eastern politics.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:justice","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000735","text":"It was only after repeated failures of their different missions they found that in every case they were out-intrigued by this innocent-looking gentleman, who below the surface was as cunning as a fox and as clever a diplomat as could be found in all the service.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000736","text":"And so it has been with us British. Foreign spies stationed in our country saw no difficulty in completely hoodwinking so stupid a people; they never supposed that the majority of them have all been known to our Secret Service Department, and carefully watched, unknown to themselves.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000737","text":"Few of them ever landed in this country without undergoing the scrutiny of an unobtrusive little old gentleman with tall hat and umbrella, but the wag of whose finger sent a detective on the heels of the visitor until his actual business and location were assured and found to be satisfactory.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000738","text":"For years the correspondence of these gentry has been regularly opened, noted, and sent on.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000739","text":"They were not as a rule worth arresting, the information sent was not of any urgent importance, and so long as they went on thinking that they were unnoticed, their superiors in their own country made no effort to send more astute men in their place.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000740","text":"Thus we knew what the enemy were looking for, and we knew what information they had received, and this as a rule was not of much account.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000741","text":"On August 4th, the day before the declaration of war, the twenty leading spies were formally arrested and over 200 of their minor agents were also taken in hand, and thus their organisation failed them at the moment when it was wanted most.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000742","text":"Steps were also taken to prevent any substitutes being appointed in their places.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000743","text":"Private wireless stations were dismantled, and by means of traps those were discovered which had not been voluntarily reported and registered.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000744","text":"It used to amuse some of us to watch the foreign spies at work on our ground.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000745","text":"One especially interested me, who set himself up ostensibly as a coal merchant, but never dealt in a single ounce of coal.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000746","text":"His daily reconnaissance of the country, his noting of the roads, and his other movements entailed in preparing his reports, were all watched and recorded.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000747","text":"His letters were opened in the post, sealed up, and sent on.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000748","text":"His friends were observed and shadowed on arriving--as they did--at Hull instead of in London.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000749","text":"And all the time he was plodding along, wasting his time, quite innocent of the fact that he was being watched, and was incidentally giving us a fine amount of information.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000750","text":"On the other hand, the exceedingly stupid Englishmen who wandered about foreign countries sketching cathedrals, or catching butterflies, or fishing for trout, were merely laughed at as harmless lunatics.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000751","text":"Some examples of secret sketches of fortresses which have been used with success are shown on the following pages.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000752","text":"[Illustration: _This sketch of a butterfly contains the outline of a fortress, and marks both the position and power of the guns. The marks on the wings between the lines mean nothing, but those on the lines show the nature and size of the guns, according to the keys below._]","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000753","text":"[Illustration: The marks on the wings reveal the shape of the fortress shown here and the size of the guns.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000754","text":"_The position of each gun is at the place inside the outline of the fort on the butterfly where the line marked with the spot ends. The head of the butterfly points towards the north._]","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000755","text":"[Illustration: _A smart piece of spy-work. Veins on an ivy leaf show the outline of the fort as seen looking west (Point of the leaf indicates north.)_]","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000756","text":"[Illustration: _Shows where big guns are mounted if a vein points to them._]","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000757","text":"[Illustration: _Shows \"dead ground,\" where there is shelter from fire._]","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000758","text":"[Illustration: _Here is another of the methods by which I concealed the plans of the forts I made._","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000759","text":"_First of all, I would sketch the plan as shown in the picture above giving the strength and positions of the various guns as shown below:_","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:resilience","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000760","text":"_A. Kaponiers with machine guns._ _B. 15 cm. gun cupola._ _C. 12 cm. guns cupolas._ _D. Q.-F. disappearing guns._ _E. Howitzer cupolas._ _F. Searchlight._]","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000761","text":"[Illustration: _Having done this, I would consider the best method of concealing my plans.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000762","text":"In this case I decided to transform the sketch into that of a stained glass window, and if you will carefully examine the picture above you will see how successfully this has been done.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000763","text":"Certain of the decorations signify the sizes and positions of the guns.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000764","text":"These signs are given below, together with their meaning._]","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000765","text":"[Illustration: _Another example of this method of making secret plans is shown here._","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000766","text":"_This sketch was made, giving all the particulars that I wanted.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000767","text":"I then decided to bury it in such a way that it could not be recognised as a fortress plan if I were caught by the military authorities.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000768","text":"One idea which occurred to me was to make it into the doorway of a cathedral or church, but I finally decided on the sketch of the moth's head.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000769","text":"Underneath in my note-book I wrote the following words:--_","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000770","text":"\"_Head of Dula moth as seen through a magnifying glass. Caught 19.5.12. Magnified about six times size of life.\" (Meaning scale of 6 inches to the mile.)_]","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000771","text":"Once I went \"butterfly hunting\" in Dalmatia. Cattaro, the capital, has been the scene of much bombarding during the present war.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000772","text":"More than a hundred years ago it was bombarded by the British fleet and taken.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000773","text":"It lies at the head of a loch some fifteen miles long, and in some parts but a few hundred yards wide, in a trough between mountains.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000774","text":"From Cattaro, at the head of the loch, a zig-zag road leads up the mountain side over the frontier into Montenegro.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000775","text":"When the British ships endeavoured to attack from the seaward, the channel was closed by chains and booms put across it.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000776","text":"But the defenders had reckoned without the resourcefulness of the British \"handyman,\" and a few days later, to the utter astonishment of the garrison, guns began to bombard them from the top of a neighbouring mountain!","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000777","text":"The British captain had landed his guns on the Adriatic shore, and by means of timber slides rigged up on the mountain side he had hauled his guns bodily up the rocky steeps to the very summit of the mountain.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000778","text":"He fixed up his batteries, and was eventually able to bombard the town with such effect that it had to surrender.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000779","text":"It was perhaps characteristic of us that we only took the town because it was held by our enemies.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000780","text":"We did not want it, and when we had got it we did not know what to do with it.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000781","text":"We therefore handed it over to the Montenegrins, and thus gave them a seaport of their own.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000782","text":"For this feat the Montenegrins have always had a feeling of admiration and of gratitude to the British, and, though by terms of ulterior treaties it was eventually handed over to Dalmatia, the Montenegrins have never forgotten our goodwill towards them on this occasion.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:gratitude","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000783","text":"But other batteries have since been built upon these mountain tops, and it was my business to investigate their positions, strength, and armaments.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","theme:resilience","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000784","text":"I went armed with most effective weapons for the purpose, which have served me well in many a similar campaign. I took a sketch-book, in which were numerous pictures--some finished, others only partly done--of butterflies of every degree and rank, from a \"Red Admiral\" to a \"Painted Lady.\"","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:creativity","theme:grief","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000785","text":"Carrying this book and a colour-box, and a butterfly net in my hand, I was above all suspicion to anyone who met me on the lonely mountain side, even in the neighbourhood of the forts.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000786","text":"I was hunting butterflies, and it was always a good introduction with which to go to anyone who was watching me with suspicion.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000787","text":"Quite frankly, with my sketch-book in hand, I would ask innocently whether he had seen such-and-such a butterfly in the neighbourhood, as I was anxious to catch one.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000788","text":"Ninety-nine out of a hundred did not know one butterfly from another--any more than I do--so one was on fairly safe ground in that way, and they thoroughly sympathised with the mad Englishman who was hunting these insects.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:justice","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000789","text":"They did not look sufficiently closely into the sketches of butterflies to notice that the delicately drawn veins of the wings were exact representations, in plan, of their own fort, and that the spots on the wings denoted the number and position of guns and their different calibres.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000790","text":"On another occasion I found it a simple disguise to go as a fisherman into the country which I wanted to examine.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000791","text":"My business was to find some passes in the mountains, and report whether they were feasible for the passage of troops. I therefore wandered up the various streams which led over the hills, and by quietly fishing about I was able to make surveys of the whole neighbourhood.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000792","text":"But on one occasion a countryman constituted himself my guide, and insisted on sticking to me all the morning, showing me places where fish could be caught.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:leadership","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000793","text":"I was not, as a matter of fact, much of a fisherman at that time, nor had I any desire to catch fish, and my tackle was of a very ramshackle description for the purpose.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000794","text":"I flogged the water assiduously with an impossible fly, just to keep the man's attention from my real work, in the hope that he would eventually get tired of it and go away.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000795","text":"He watched me with the greatest interest for a long time, and eventually explained that he did not know anything about fly fishing, but had a much better system of getting the fish together before casting a worm or slug-among-them.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000796","text":"His system he then proceeded to demonstrate, which was to spit into the water. This certainly attracted a run of fish, and then he said that if only he had a worm he could catch any number.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000797","text":"I eventually got rid of him by sending him to procure such, and while he was away I made myself scarce and clambered over the ridge to another valley.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000798","text":"Spying brings with it a constant wearing strain of nerves and mind, seeing that it involves certain death for a false step in war or imprisonment in peace.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","theme:mortality","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000799","text":"The Government promises to give no help whatever to its servant if caught.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:leadership","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"saadi-ext-000800","text":"He is warned to keep no notes, to confide in no one, to use disguises where necessary, and to shift for himself entirely.","author":"Saadi","source":"Bustan — Rehatsek Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."}]}